Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.16,0:20:09.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Thank you. - Now, sir, tell me your troubles.\N{\rCHT}- 謝謝 - 你可以向我盡吐煩惱{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.45,0:20:13.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, my wife has me between a rock and a hard place.\N{\rCHT}我老婆把我逼得走投無路{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.83,0:20:15.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's her job. You should respect that.\N{\rCHT}那是她的職責 應予尊重{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.33,0:20:19.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,When I first met Marylin, we were crazy about each other.\N{\rCHT}我結識瑪麗蓮不久 就和她打得火熱{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.01,0:20:23.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not emotionally, of course. Just we couldn't keep our hands off each other.\N{\rCHT}我不是指心靈上 但我們總是如膠似漆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.63,0:20:26.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,But then... Then...\N{\rCHT}可是後來… 後來…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:32.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Time marches on. Ardor cools. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 後來事過境遷 熱情冷卻 - 對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.81,0:20:36.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,So we had an understanding.\N{\rCHT}於是 我們互相諒解{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.15,0:20:39.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Whereby? - We could see other people.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼諒解？- 各自結交異性{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.15,0:20:43.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Has Mrs. Rexroth pursued the opportunities implicit in your arrangement?\N{\rCHT}雷克諾斯太太有沒有結交？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.97,0:20:46.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can only assume.\N{\rCHT}我只能假設{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.16,0:20:49.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not in court you can't. Has she retained counsel?\N{\rCHT}庭上不能假設 她有沒有律師？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:52.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know. She has Rottweilers.\N{\rCHT}不知道 她有幾頭惡狗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.75,0:20:58.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not a good sign. And have you, yourself, exploited your understood freedom?\N{\rCHT}那不是好現象 你自己有沒有去結交異性？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.00,0:21:05.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's a lady, a young lady. She lets me be myself.\N{\rCHT}我結交了一位小姐 她對我體貼入微{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.43,0:21:10.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course. And your wife is aware and/or has evidence?\N{\rCHT}當然 太太有沒有掌握到證據？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.43,0:21:11.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Video. - Ha!\N{\rCHT}錄影帶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.27,0:21:18.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,To cut to the chase, forensically speaking, is there a prenup?\N{\rCHT}讓我單刀直入問一句 你有沒有婚前協議？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.65,0:21:28.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,"The fault, dear Brutus, lies not in our stars, but in ourselves."\N{\rCHT}"天作孽猶可違 自作孽不可活"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.24,0:21:31.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you this, what kind of a settlement do you seek?\N{\rCHT}你希望達成什麼協議？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:35.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are, for you, the parameters of the possible?\N{\rCHT}你願意給她多少？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.21,0:21:39.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that's the problem. I can't afford to give her anything.\N{\rCHT}問題是 我什麼都不能給她{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.42,0:21:44.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nothing?\N{\rCHT}分文不給？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.55,0:21:46.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah, I know that sounds a little rough,\N{\rCHT}說來有點不近人情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.47,0:21:50.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,but, listen, I'm about to close a deal to develop some mini-malls.\N{\rCHT}不過 我正在開發購物商場{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.55,0:21:52.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am mortgaged up to my heinie.\N{\rCHT}所以把全部資產都押給銀行{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.39,0:21:55.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,If this deal goes south, I am ruined. I will lose millions.\N{\rCHT}假如生意做不成 我就破產了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.11,0:22:01.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you propose that, in spite of demonstrable infidelity on your part,\N{\rCHT}你的意思是 你拈花惹草 被人抓住把柄{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.94,0:22:06.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,your unoffending wife should be tossed out on her ear.\N{\rCHT}反而要把正經的妻子逐出家門{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.15,0:22:09.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, is that possible?\N{\rCHT}有沒有可能？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.79,0:22:15.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a challenge.\N{\rCHT}有挑戰性{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.95,0:22:19.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why don't you come out to Malibu and see my new beach house tomorrow?\N{\rCHT}明天來參觀我在馬里布的海灘別墅吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.75,0:22:21.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,I didn't know Dimitri had a beach house.\N{\rCHT}我怎麼不知道狄米崔有海灘別墅{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.90,0:22:23.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Neither did I until my lawyer found it.\N{\rCHT}我的律師好不容易查出來的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.75,0:22:26.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Quite a paper trail. Had it in the dog's name.\N{\rCHT}真是大工程 是用狗的名義買的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.05,0:22:30.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, tomorrow won't work. I'm having a body wrap. How's Wednesday?\N{\rCHT}明天我要做護膚 星期三怎樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.51,0:22:32.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hair appointment in the morning. Afternoon?\N{\rCHT}早上要做頭髮 下午呢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.26,0:22:34.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shrink. How's your Thursday?\N{\rCHT}要看心理醫生 星期四呢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.43,0:22:37.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm having facial injections. That kills Friday and Saturday.\N{\rCHT}要注射除皺紋針 所以星期五和星期六也不能出門{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.18,0:22:39.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,- BOTOX? - Butt fat.\N{\rCHT}- 肉毒桿菌？- 屁股脂肪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.60,0:22:42.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Does that really work? - You tell me.\N{\rCHT}- 效果怎樣？- 你認為呢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.40,0:22:43.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello, darlings.\N{\rCHT}大家好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.61,0:22:49.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, you and Rex are...\N{\rCHT}你和雷克斯…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.75,0:22:54.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, as my private investigator put it, "We're gonna nail his ass."\N{\rCHT}正如私家偵探說的 "把他逮個正著"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.37,0:22:58.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to nail George's ass for years, but he is so careful.\N{\rCHT}我捉喬治痛腳捉了好多年 但他總是小心翼翼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.33,0:23:05.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Are you all right, Claire? - Down the wrong pipe.\N{\rCHT}- 克萊兒 你沒事吧？- 嗆到了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.26,0:23:09.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So who's your lawyer? - Freddy Bender.\N{\rCHT}- 你的律師是誰？- 佛萊迪班德{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.47,0:23:12.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have an appointment this afternoon with Rex and his schnauzer.\N{\rCHT}今天下午要見雷克斯 和他的無名律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.80,0:23:15.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So who's Rex's guy? - Miles Massey.\N{\rCHT}- 雷克斯的律師是誰？- 邁爾斯梅西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.43,0:23:18.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles Massey? Of Massey Myerson?\N{\rCHT}梅西邁爾森的邁爾斯梅西？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.60,0:23:20.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you know him? - By reputation,\N{\rCHT}- 你認識他？- 聽過他大名{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.56,0:23:23.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,and, Marylin, he's no schnauzer.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 他不是無名小卒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.69,0:23:26.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,He got Phyllis Rumsey that cute little island of George's.\N{\rCHT}他替菲莉絲拉姆西贏得 喬治的私人小島{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.65,0:23:29.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,George was so impressed, he hired him when he divorced his second.\N{\rCHT}喬治很驚訝 所以跟第二任離婚時雇用他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.32,0:23:31.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Muriel Rumsey. - Who's she?\N{\rCHT}- 繆莉兒拉姆西 - 她做什麼的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.91,0:23:34.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now? Night manager at McDonald's.\N{\rCHT}她現在慘到要做麥當勞夜班{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.20,0:23:38.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, Marylin, do we have a man for you.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 介紹個男人給你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.16,0:23:41.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thorstenson Gieselensen.\N{\rCHT}托斯添森基斯蘭森{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.08,0:23:43.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He just separated from his third. - He's in fish.\N{\rCHT}- 剛剛離婚第三次 - 是漁業大亨{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.96,0:23:45.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He is fish. - Well, he's tuna.\N{\rCHT}- 他是大魚 - 他是黑鮪魚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.71,0:23:48.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ladies, I'm not seeing anyone until I've finished nailing Rex's ass.\N{\rCHT}我要先釘死雷克斯 才找另一個男人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.88,0:23:51.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, Marylin, this man is tuna.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 這是條黑鮪魚耶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.80,0:23:55.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sarah, one husband at a time.\N{\rCHT}莎拉 嫁老公只能一次一個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.81,0:24:00.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll do the talking. I know you'll be tempted to chime in,\N{\rCHT}由我來談判 你會想插嘴{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:03.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,but remember that you're in an emotionally vulnerable state.\N{\rCHT}但記得你的情緒受到打擊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.02,0:24:07.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm the professional. - Oh. Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 我是專家 - 好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.19,0:24:09.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy.\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.82,0:24:15.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy Bender, this is Rex Rexroth.\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪班德 這位是雷克斯雷克諾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.05,0:24:16.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you are the lovely Marylin.\N{\rCHT}你一定是迷人的瑪麗蓮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.03,0:24:20.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please, Ms. Rexroth. And you must be Mr. Massey.\N{\rCHT}請叫我雷克諾斯小姐 你一定是梅西先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.95,0:24:23.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please, Miles. Sit. Sit down.\N{\rCHT}叫邁爾斯就好了 請坐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.92,0:24:29.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy, I was sorry to hear about the Goldberger award. Pastry?\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪 葛柏格那宗官司你不要介意 吃點心嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.97,0:24:36.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,We did very well. We did very well.\N{\rCHT}那宗官司我們打得很好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.18,0:24:38.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not to worry, Mrs. Rexroth, you're ably represented.\N{\rCHT}放心 雷克諾斯太太 你所托得人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.72,0:24:42.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Freddy's just too modest to tell you he used to clerk for Clarence Thomas.\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪太謙虛了 他以前在 克拉倫斯湯瑪斯的手下做過事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.52,0:24:44.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Pastry? Going begging.\N{\rCHT}吃甜點嗎？儘量吃啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.68,0:24:49.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't try to bait me, Miles. Now if you have a proposal to make, let's hear it.\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 別想套我 有建議儘管提出來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.32,0:24:53.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, at this point, my client is still prepared to consider reconciliation.\N{\rCHT}我的客戶仍願意考慮和解{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.61,0:24:56.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client has ruled that out.\N{\rCHT}不可能{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.87,0:24:59.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client is prepared to entertain an amicable dissolution\N{\rCHT}我的客戶準備好辦理{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.45,0:25:02.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,- of the marriage without prejudice. - That's a fart in a stiff wind.\N{\rCHT}- 無過失離婚手續 - 聽你在放屁{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.50,0:25:04.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client proposes a 30-day cooling-off period.\N{\rCHT}我的客戶要有冷靜期{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.92,0:25:07.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client feels sufficiently dispassionate.\N{\rCHT}我的客戶已經夠冷靜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.08,0:25:09.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client asks that you not initiate proceedings\N{\rCHT}我的客戶請你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.25,0:25:11.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,pending his setting certain affairs in order.\N{\rCHT}延後提出離婚訴訟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.30,0:25:17.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What's so goddamn funny? - Please, let me handle this.\N{\rCHT}- 有什麼好笑？- 讓我來處理{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.06,0:25:21.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. So much for the icebreakers. What are you after, Freddy?\N{\rCHT}開場白講完了 佛萊迪 你要什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.97,0:25:25.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client is prepared to settle for 50% of the marital assets.\N{\rCHT}我的客戶要五成財產{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.81,0:25:30.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why only 50, Freddy? Why not 100?\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪 只要五成？為什麼不要十成？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.22,0:25:34.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,While we're dreaming, why not 150%? Are you familiar with Kershner?\N{\rCHT}要做夢的話 為什麼不要十五成？你熟悉凱斯納案嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.49,0:25:35.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Kershner does not apply.\N{\rCHT}凱斯納案不適用{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.70,0:25:37.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bring this to trial, we'll see if Kershner applies.\N{\rCHT}不妨由法庭決定{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.49,0:25:39.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What's Kershner? - Please, let me handle this.\N{\rCHT}- 凱斯納案是什麼？- 讓我處理{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.57,0:25:41.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Kershner was in Kentucky. - Kershner was in Kentucky?\N{\rCHT}- 凱斯納案發生在肯德基 - 凱斯納案發生在肯德基？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.04,0:25:43.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Kershner was in Kentucky! - All right, Freddy.\N{\rCHT}- 凱斯納案發生在肯德基 - 好 佛萊迪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.04,0:25:46.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forget Kershner. What's your bottom line?\N{\rCHT}算了 你的底線是什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.08,0:25:47.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Primary residence, 30% of remaining assets.\N{\rCHT}住宅 其餘資產的三成{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.04,0:25:51.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you, nuts? Have you forgotten Kershner?\N{\rCHT}你瘋了嗎？你忘了凱斯納案了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.63,0:25:56.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Freddy. It's a negotiation. - See you at the preliminary.\N{\rCHT}- 佛萊迪 現在我們在商量啊 - 法庭上再見{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.63,0:26:01.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy, we're all friends here. It's a negotiation. Hey!\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪 大家都是朋友嘛 我們在商量啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.64,0:26:06.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy! Fine. We'll eat the pastry.\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪 好吧 甜點我們自己吃{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:17.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,I thought that went well.\N{\rCHT}這個會開得不錯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.70,0:26:22.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\N{\rCHT}好耶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.16,0:26:25.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Gus, you outdid yourself.\N{\rCHT}蓋斯 你做得真妙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.54,0:26:32.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Let's go back to the football game. - Kiss my ass.\N{\rCHT}- 轉回去看球賽吧 - 誰理你啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.42,0:26:35.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's halftime, man. This is some good shit.\N{\rCHT}現在是中場時間 這個好看{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.10,0:26:36.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm about to nail his ass, right here.\N{\rCHT}我快要逮到他了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.80,0:26:38.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, Gussy, go back to the Rabinowitz tape again.\N{\rCHT}蓋斯 再看一次拉比諾維茨的影片{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.84,0:26:40.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hold on. Now here come the good part.\N{\rCHT}等等 這是精彩部分{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.39,0:26:41.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look at this.\N{\rCHT}快瞧瞧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.55,0:26:45.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,- She about to take off her panties. - Yeah. Come on, come on, come on.\N{\rCHT}- 她快要脫內褲了 - 快點脫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.68,0:26:48.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Gus? - Mmm-mmm. Yeah?\N{\rCHT}- 蓋斯？- 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.35,0:26:50.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's Miles Massey. - Take a number.\N{\rCHT}- 邁爾斯梅西找你 - 抄下電話號碼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.85,0:26:53.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's about a job tonight. -God damn it!\N{\rCHT}- 他要你今晚出動 - 該死的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.94,0:26:57.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit, did you see that?\N{\rCHT}有沒有見到？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.34,0:27:15.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here we are.\N{\rCHT}這邊請{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.42,0:27:19.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ms. Rexroth. I am so delighted you decided to come.\N{\rCHT}雷克諾斯小姐 很高興你賞臉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.80,0:27:24.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I must admit, I was curious. - Something to start. Some wine, perhaps?\N{\rCHT}- 我是出於好奇 - 先來點餐前酒嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.51,0:27:27.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,-Red? -French.\N{\rCHT}- 紅酒？- 法國{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.02,0:27:29.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Bordeaux? - Chateau Margaux.\N{\rCHT}- 波爾多？- 瑪哥堡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.68,0:27:31.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,- '57? - '59.\N{\rCHT}- 1957年？- 1959年{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.02,0:27:34.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- '54. - Mr. Massey.\N{\rCHT}- 1954年 - 梅西先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.98,0:27:36.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good, sir.\N{\rCHT}好的 先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.32,0:27:37.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your husband had told me\N{\rCHT}你丈夫認為{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.04,0:27:41.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,you were the most beautiful woman that he'd ever met.\N{\rCHT}你是絕色美女{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.91,0:27:45.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect the most beautiful woman I'd ever met.\N{\rCHT}想不到他沒有言過其實{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.08,0:27:49.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Dismiss your vows, your feigned tears, your flattery.\N{\rCHT}虛情假意 豈能當真{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.04,0:27:52.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,"For where a heart is hard, they make no battery."\N{\rCHT}"言不由衷 如何動容"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.04,0:27:59.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Who ever loved that loved not at first sight?"\N{\rCHT}"一見鍾情 方可言情"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.84,0:28:03.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now you didn't ask me here to pick me up. You could be disbarred for that.\N{\rCHT}你如果勾搭我 會被吊銷律師執照{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.40,0:28:06.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm reckless.\N{\rCHT}也許我喜歡冒險{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.39,0:28:08.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,What was your performance about this afternoon?\N{\rCHT}今天見面時你在玩什麼把戲？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.31,0:28:09.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,What did your lawyer say?\N{\rCHT}你的律師怎麼說？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.81,0:28:13.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, Freddy thinks you're a buffoon. He says you've been too successful.\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪說你是小丑 他說你事業太過順利了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.06,0:28:17.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're bored, complacent, and you're on your way down.\N{\rCHT}變得無趣 自滿 快要走向失敗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.82,0:28:19.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- But you don't think so. - How do you know?\N{\rCHT}- 可是你不同意 - 你怎麼知道？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.94,0:28:21.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Why would you be here? - Why did you ask me?\N{\rCHT}- 為什麼赴約？- 為什麼問我？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.07,0:28:23.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Can't I be curious? - About what?\N{\rCHT}- 好奇不行嗎？- 好奇什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.57,0:28:26.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you ever answer questions? - Do you?\N{\rCHT}- 你一向以問作答？- 你呢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.12,0:28:28.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll have the tournedos of beef. The lady will have the same. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}我要一客嫩牛排 女士也一樣 謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.74,0:28:30.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\N{\rCHT}謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.83,0:28:33.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,I assume you're a carnivore.\N{\rCHT}你應該是肉食主義者吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.21,0:28:36.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Massey, you have no idea.\N{\rCHT}梅西先生 我胃口奇佳{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.51,0:28:38.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles, please.\N{\rCHT}請叫我邁爾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.96,0:28:41.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell me more about yourself.\N{\rCHT}講講你自己好嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.46,0:28:46.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, Miles. Let me tell you everything that you need to know.\N{\rCHT}好 邁爾斯 我不妨坦白告訴你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.89,0:28:50.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,You may think you're tough, but I eat men like you for breakfast.\N{\rCHT}你自以為了不起 但我根本不把你放在眼內{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.88,0:28:53.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've invested five good years in my marriage to Rex,\N{\rCHT}我投資了五年的時間做雷克斯老婆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.44,0:28:56.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,and I've nailed his ass fair and square.\N{\rCHT}終於被我逮到他的痛腳 證據確鑿{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.65,0:28:59.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to have it stuffed, mounted,\N{\rCHT}我現在要收割成果{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.19,0:29:01.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,and have my lady friends come over and throw darts at it.\N{\rCHT}找女性好友們來開派對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.03,0:29:03.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Man hater, huh?\N{\rCHT}你憎恨男人？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.90,0:29:07.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,People don't go on safaris 'cause they hate animals.\N{\rCHT}獵人打獵不是因為憎恨野獸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.74,0:29:10.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,So it's just for the hunt with the trophy at the end?\N{\rCHT}原來你是為了獵物和獎賞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.70,0:29:12.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,No. Nothing so frivolous.\N{\rCHT}不是那樣瑣碎的事情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.83,0:29:19.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,This divorce means money. Money means independence.\N{\rCHT}離婚帶來財富 財富帶來獨立{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.88,0:29:22.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm after.\N{\rCHT}我要的是獨立{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.46,0:29:24.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you after, Miles?\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 你要的是什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.76,0:29:28.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm a lot like you. Just looking for an ass to mount.\N{\rCHT}我跟你很像 一心尋找獵物{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.64,0:29:33.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, don't look at mine.\N{\rCHT}不必打我的主意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.20,0:29:47.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Two, three.\N{\rCHT}好 二 三{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.81,0:30:17.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,I got you. See this?\N{\rCHT}沒轍了吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.33,0:30:33.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\N{\rCHT}要什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.95,0:30:40.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll just have a salad, please. Baby field greens.\N{\rCHT}我只要一客沙拉 要很嫩的青菜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.29,0:30:42.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,What did you call me?\N{\rCHT}你嫌我老？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.09,0:30:46.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't call you anything.\N{\rCHT}我沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.11,0:30:50.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You want a salad. - Do you have a green salad?\N{\rCHT}- 你要沙拉 - 有沒有綠色沙拉？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.93,0:30:55.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What the fuck color would it be? - Why are we eating here?\N{\rCHT}- 不然沙拉還會有什麼鬼顏色？- 為什麼要來這裡？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.10,0:30:56.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's his problem?\N{\rCHT}他有什麼問題？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.98,0:30:59.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just bring him an iceberg lettuce and a mealy tomato wedge\N{\rCHT}給他來客番茄生菜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.06,0:31:02.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,smothered with French dressing.\N{\rCHT}法式沙拉醬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.31,0:31:03.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,And for you?\N{\rCHT}你呢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.75,0:31:07.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ham sandwich on stale rye bread. Lots of mayo, easy on the ham.\N{\rCHT}火腿裸麥三明治 美奶滋多一點 火腿少一點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.28,0:31:09.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Slaw cup? - What the hell.\N{\rCHT}- 要沙拉嗎？- 無所謂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.73,0:31:10.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello, Marge.\N{\rCHT}你好 瑪姬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.99,0:31:13.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How are you, Gus? - I'm all right.\N{\rCHT}- 蓋斯 你好嗎？- 還算好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.78,0:31:18.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay. Now, I minoxed her address book.\N{\rCHT}我翻拍了她的電話簿{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.16,0:31:20.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't call me anymore for this penny-ante shit.\N{\rCHT}以後這種小事不要煩我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.29,0:31:24.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I shoot action. Me and the lkegami, Jack. - Thank you, Gus.\N{\rCHT}- 我跟我的寶貝攝影機專拍動作片 - 謝謝 蓋斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.88,0:31:28.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,- And those Rottweilers were a menace, man. - I told you she had dogs.\N{\rCHT}- 而且那幾隻狗太殘暴了 - 我說過她有狗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.76,0:31:32.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But you didn't tell me they had a hard-on for anus africanus.\N{\rCHT}對 可是你沒說狗跟黑人有仇{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.26,0:31:35.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Gus. Did you see any evidence?\N{\rCHT}蓋斯 你有沒有發現證據？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.31,0:31:40.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Any "telltale signs" of indiscretion on the part of Ms. Rexroth?\N{\rCHT}雷克諾斯小姐 婚外情的"蛛絲馬跡"？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.84,0:31:46.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about "telltale signs"? Look, I see an ass, I nail it.\N{\rCHT}"蛛絲馬跡"是什麼意思？我見到痛腳就捉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.86,0:31:50.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't sneak around sniffing the sheets. God damn it, I'm Gus Petch!\N{\rCHT}我不會去偷聞別人的床單 我可是蓋斯派奇{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.45,0:31:54.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Couldn't you be disbarred for that? - Oh, I don't think so.\N{\rCHT}- 你不怕被吊銷執照？- 不會{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.99,0:31:57.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Maybe if I'd had the patty melt. - You had a guy break into her house\N{\rCHT}- 除非我吃了天堂漢堡 - 你叫他私闖民宅{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.87,0:32:00.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,- and photograph her address book. - No, Wrigley.\N{\rCHT}- 偷拍電話簿 - 雷格利 我沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.33,0:32:04.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I happened to let a man know that I was interested in her address book.\N{\rCHT}我只是跟他說 我對她的電話簿有興趣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.17,0:32:05.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's not criminal.\N{\rCHT}這樣沒犯法{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.21,0:32:07.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I also happened to let him know that I was taking her out to dinner.\N{\rCHT}我還跟他說我要請她出去吃晚餐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.05,0:32:13.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's not a crime either. No, I don't see myself as culpable in any sense.\N{\rCHT}這樣也沒犯法 我完全是清白的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.09,0:32:15.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,You, on the other hand, could be disbarred\N{\rCHT}而你卻不一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.35,0:32:18.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,for developing and examining these photos of her address book.\N{\rCHT}你把照片洗出來 可能會被吊銷執照{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.68,0:32:22.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't really concern me.\N{\rCHT}不過那不關我的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.10,0:32:26.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Right. Who are you looking for? - Tenzing Norgay.\N{\rCHT}- 你想在電話簿上找到什麼人？- 丹增諾傑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.65,0:32:30.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tenzing Norgay. That's someone she slept with.\N{\rCHT}丹增諾傑 她的情夫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.65,0:32:32.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,I doubt it. Tenzing Norgay was the Sherpa\N{\rCHT}應該不是 丹增諾傑是協助艾德蒙希拉瑞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.03,0:32:35.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,that helped Edmund Hillary climb Mount Everest.\N{\rCHT}成功攀登聖母峰的嚮導{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.11,0:32:37.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,And Marylin knows him.\N{\rCHT}而瑪麗蓮認識他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.33,0:32:40.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, you idiot. Not the Tenzing Norgay. Her Tenzing Norgay.\N{\rCHT}白癡 不是那個丹增諾傑 是瑪麗蓮的丹增諾傑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.54,0:32:44.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure that I actually follow that.\N{\rCHT}我不明白{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.08,0:32:48.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Few great accomplishments are achieved single-handedly, Wrigley.\N{\rCHT}雷格利 獨力難成大事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.13,0:32:50.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Most have their Norgays.\N{\rCHT}多數人有諾傑從旁協助{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.25,0:32:54.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin Rexroth is even now climbing her Everest.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯也在攀登聖母峰{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.18,0:32:55.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wanna find her Norgay.\N{\rCHT}我想查出她的諾傑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.47,0:32:57.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,But how do you determine which of the people on here are...\N{\rCHT}但怎能決定誰是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.05,0:33:00.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How do you spot a Norgay? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 你怎麼知道誰是諾傑？- 對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.68,0:33:02.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,You start with the people with the funny names.\N{\rCHT}從那些奇怪的姓名下手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.89,0:33:04.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yea, oh yea!\N{\rCHT}從那些奇怪的姓名下手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.14,0:33:06.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Family Court of the Fifth District of Los Angeles County now in session.\N{\rCHT}洛杉磯第五區家庭法庭開庭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.02,0:33:09.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Honorable Marva Munson presiding. All rise.\N{\rCHT}慕華莫森法官主審 各位起立{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.07,0:33:19.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Have you sat before her before?\N{\rCHT}你們有沒有在她的庭前坐過？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.90,0:33:22.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,No. No, the judge sits first. Then we sit.\N{\rCHT}沒有 法官先坐 我們才坐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.62,0:33:25.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well, have you sat after her before? - "Sat after her before?"\N{\rCHT}- 你們有沒有在她之後坐過？- "在她之後坐過"？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.83,0:33:27.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,You mean, "Have we argued before her before?"\N{\rCHT}你是指 "我們有沒有在她的庭上辯過？"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.83,0:33:31.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,The judge sits in judgment. The counsel argues before the judge.\N{\rCHT}法官審案 律師在法官前辯案{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.09,0:33:33.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,So have you argued before her before?\N{\rCHT}那你們有沒有在她面前辯過案？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.76,0:33:35.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Before her before, or before she sat before?\N{\rCHT}在她之前還是在她坐下之前？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.80,0:33:36.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Before her before.\N{\rCHT}在她之前{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.97,0:33:39.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I said, "Before her before." - No, you said, "Before she sat before."\N{\rCHT}- 我說 "在她之前" - 不 你說 "在她坐下之前"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.01,0:33:41.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I did at first, but... - Look, don't argue.\N{\rCHT}- 我先說… - 不要辯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.06,0:33:44.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm not. - No, you don't argue. We argue.\N{\rCHT}- 我沒有 - 你不辯 我們才辯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.27,0:33:45.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Counsel argues. - You appear.\N{\rCHT}- 律師辯案 - 你出庭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.69,0:33:47.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,The judge sits. Then you sit.\N{\rCHT}- 法官先坐 - 你後坐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.10,0:33:49.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Or you stand in contempt. - And then we argue.\N{\rCHT}- 或是故意不坐來藐視 - 然後我們辯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.36,0:33:51.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,- The counsel argues. - Which you've done before.\N{\rCHT}- 律師辯 - 你們以前辯過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.61,0:33:54.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Which we've done before. - Ah.\N{\rCHT}我們以前辯過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.15,0:33:55.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,But not before her.\N{\rCHT}不過不是在她之前{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.41,0:34:00.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Rex. Sit.\N{\rCHT}雷克斯 坐下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.74,0:34:02.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,There it is! I got it!\N{\rCHT}就是這樣 拍到了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.12,0:34:07.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna nail your ass. I'm gonna nail your ass.\N{\rCHT}把你逮個正著 把你逮個正著{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.37,0:34:09.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna nail your ass. Yeah!\N{\rCHT}把你逮個正著 耶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.88,0:34:12.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm gonna nail your ass. - It's a silly misunderstanding.\N{\rCHT}- 把你逮個正著 - 這是一場誤會{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.55,0:34:14.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get that thing off me now!\N{\rCHT}別拍了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.96,0:34:16.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm gonna nail your ass.\N{\rCHT}把你逮個正著{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.59,0:34:20.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna nail your ass. I'm gonna nail your ass.\N{\rCHT}把你逮個正著 把你逮個正著{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.19,0:34:34.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Devastated. Simply devastated.\N{\rCHT}逮個正著 簡直是晴天霹靂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.32,0:34:38.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mrs. Rexroth.\N{\rCHT}謝謝 雷克諾斯太太{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.07,0:34:43.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Massey, any questions?\N{\rCHT}梅西先生 有沒有問題？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.98,0:35:17.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Dismiss your vows, your feigned tears, your flattery.\N{\rCHT}虛情假意 豈能當真{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.53,0:35:20.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,"For where a heart is hard, they make no battery."\N{\rCHT}"言不由衷 如何動容"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.40,0:35:23.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Mrs. Rexroth, do you know those lines? - Objection, Your Honor.\N{\rCHT}- 雷克諾斯太太 認識這幾句話嗎？- 庭上 反對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.32,0:35:26.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Grounds? - Poetry recitation.\N{\rCHT}- 原因？- 朗誦詩句{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.08,0:35:33.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me rephrase. Mrs. Rexroth, how high is that wall around your heart?\N{\rCHT}我重問一次 雷克諾斯太太 你的城府有多深？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.88,0:35:39.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your Honor, this is harassment, and frankly, it's still a little arty-farty.\N{\rCHT}庭上 這是騷擾 坦白說 有點矯揉造作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:41.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Rephrase. Mrs. Rexroth, have you ever been in love?\N{\rCHT}我重問一次 雷克諾斯太太 你有沒有戀愛過？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.51,0:35:43.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes. Of course.\N{\rCHT}當然有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.85,0:35:47.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,With Rex.\N{\rCHT}跟雷克斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.52,0:35:49.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you've always loved him?\N{\rCHT}你一直都愛他？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.39,0:35:53.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Who ever loved that loved not at first sight?"\N{\rCHT}"一見鍾情 方可言情"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.86,0:36:02.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,So it's your sworn testimony that you have loved Rex Rexroth\N{\rCHT}所以你發誓 你和雷克斯雷克諾斯從見面開始{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.07,0:36:04.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,since first you met?\N{\rCHT}就真心相愛？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.87,0:36:08.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.50,0:36:12.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.63,0:36:16.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,No further questions, Your Honor.\N{\rCHT}庭上 沒有問題了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.42,0:36:19.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Who's next, Mr. Bender? - We rest, Your Honor.\N{\rCHT}- 班德先生 下一位是誰？- 沒有了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.42,0:36:21.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Massey.\N{\rCHT}梅西先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.13,0:36:24.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your Honor, I call Heinz, the Baron Krauss von Espy.\N{\rCHT}庭上 傳召克勞斯馮艾斯比男爵漢斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.09,0:36:33.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Heinz, the Baron Krauss von Espy.\N{\rCHT}克勞斯馮艾斯比男爵漢斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.28,0:36:34.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Heinz, the Baron Krauss von Espy.\N{\rCHT}克勞斯馮艾斯比男爵漢斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.68,0:36:35.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Problem?\N{\rCHT}有麻煩？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.81,0:36:36.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Puffy.\N{\rCHT}皮條客{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.90,0:36:40.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Heinz, the Baron Krauss von Espy! - Tenzing Norgay.\N{\rCHT}- 克勞斯馮艾斯比男爵漢斯 - 丹增諾傑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.38,0:37:06.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Mr. Krauss, do you solemnly swear that... - Krauss von Espy.\N{\rCHT}- 克勞斯先生 願不願意… - 克勞斯馮艾斯比{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.30,0:37:08.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Krauss von Espy, do you solemnly...\N{\rCHT}克勞斯馮艾斯比先生 願不願意…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.71,0:37:10.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Baron Krauss von Espy.\N{\rCHT}克勞斯馮艾斯比男爵{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.26,0:37:11.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Solemnly swear that the testimony you are about to give\N{\rCHT}願不願意發誓{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.77,0:37:12.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,shall be the truth, the whole truth\N{\rCHT}你的供詞是事實？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.98,0:37:14.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,nothing but the truth, so help you God?\N{\rCHT}並無虛言{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.23,0:37:16.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,No maybes.\N{\rCHT}不能也許{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.81,0:37:18.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,But of course, yes.\N{\rCHT}當然願意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.98,0:37:22.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,- The Baron does not lie. - Have a seat, sir.\N{\rCHT}- 本男爵不說謊 - 請坐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.11,0:37:25.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Did you sleep with him? - Don't be a fool.\N{\rCHT}- 你和他睡過？- 別傻了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.70,0:37:28.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shh. Elsbieta.\N{\rCHT}愛斯比安達{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.58,0:37:33.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Baron von Espy, what is your profession?\N{\rCHT}馮艾斯比男爵 你做哪一行？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.00,0:37:36.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Silly man. I am a baron.\N{\rCHT}傻瓜 我是男爵嘛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.87,0:37:42.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, but do you not also hold a day job, paying job, a square job?\N{\rCHT}是 不過你有一份 有報酬的正當工作吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.17,0:37:44.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, one has to live.\N{\rCHT}人總要謀生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.34,0:37:47.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am the concierge of Les Pantalons Rouges\N{\rCHT}我在瑞士烏利白格鎮的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.51,0:37:50.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,at Bad-Gadesbourg in the canton of Uri.\N{\rCHT}畔達龍大飯店擔任客戶服務員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.76,0:37:53.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,And what does that job entail?\N{\rCHT}你負責什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.35,0:37:56.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I satisfy such requests as the clientele may present.\N{\rCHT}滿足客人需求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.69,0:37:58.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Towels, ice, et cetera?\N{\rCHT}拿毛巾冰塊之類的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.69,0:38:00.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have bellmen for that. No, no, no.\N{\rCHT}那些差事有侍應做 不 不 不{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.82,0:38:05.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Such requests that, were you at home, you would address not to your valet,\N{\rCHT}特別的請求 非心腹手下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.36,0:38:07.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,but to your majordomo.\N{\rCHT}不會委託的那種請求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.74,0:38:11.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,I see. Baron, do you recognize that woman?\N{\rCHT}男爵 你認不認識那位元女士？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.29,0:38:14.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Chere Marylin. But of course.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 當然認識{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.62,0:38:16.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look who is here. Hi!\N{\rCHT}打個招呼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.46,0:38:22.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,And she was a guest of the Red Trousers?\N{\rCHT}她曾經是畔達龍大飯店的客人？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.63,0:38:28.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, many times for relaxing and making Alpine recreation.\N{\rCHT}常客 來休閒滑雪度假{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.01,0:38:35.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am curious about her visit of five years ago. January, 1998.\N{\rCHT}五年前 1998年1月 那次她住進貴飯店{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.60,0:38:39.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can you remember any specific request she made at that time?\N{\rCHT}記得她有提出什麼特別請求嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.69,0:38:41.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can.\N{\rCHT}記得{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.19,0:38:44.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,And what, at that time, did she tell you she required?\N{\rCHT}她說她需要什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.40,0:38:49.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,She said that she required a husband!\N{\rCHT}她說她需要一位元丈夫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.87,0:38:55.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you want some bones, huh? Does Elsbieta want some bones?\N{\rCHT}要狗骨頭？愛斯比安達要狗骨頭？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.33,0:38:57.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Has anyone any bones?\N{\rCHT}誰有狗骨頭？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.29,0:39:01.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Does anyone have any bones? Bones? Dog candies?\N{\rCHT}誰有狗骨頭？狗糖？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.25,0:39:05.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, they are not candies. Milk-Bones. Hard, crunchy bones for the teeth.\N{\rCHT}不是糖 是骨頭 給狗咬的骨頭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.38,0:39:06.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hard...\N{\rCHT}硬的…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.97,0:39:10.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll attend to the dog later.\N{\rCHT}等等再管狗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.59,0:39:13.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, Baron... Where were we?\N{\rCHT}男爵… 剛才說到哪裡？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.73,0:39:19.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,"She said that she required a husband.\N{\rCHT}她說她需要一位元丈夫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.77,0:39:23.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Do you want some bones? Does Elsbieta want some bones?\N{\rCHT}要狗骨頭？愛斯比安達要狗骨頭？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.15,0:39:25.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Has anyone any bones? Hard, crunchy bones for the..."\N{\rCHT}"誰有狗骨頭？給狗咬的骨頭… "{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.78,0:39:26.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right.\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.03,0:39:31.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, a husband. That's an unusual request.\N{\rCHT}一位丈夫 真是不尋常的請求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.66,0:39:34.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did she specify what kind of a husband she was looking for?\N{\rCHT}她有沒有注明哪一類丈夫？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.45,0:39:35.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Stop him. - Objection.\N{\rCHT}- 讓他閉嘴 - 反對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.08,0:39:39.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Grounds? - Hearsay.\N{\rCHT}- 原因？- 只是傳聞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.46,0:39:40.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not secondhand, Your Honor.\N{\rCHT}庭上 這是第一手資料{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.62,0:39:43.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is direct testimony about the Baron's own conversation.\N{\rCHT}男爵在轉述自己的談話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.50,0:39:44.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm going to allow it.\N{\rCHT}我批准{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.92,0:39:49.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,She said she wanted a very rich husband.\N{\rCHT}她指定要金龜婿{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.59,0:39:55.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,She wanted to know the businesses and the wealths-es... The wealths-es.\N{\rCHT}她想知道我們的貴客 富貴的人客{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.26,0:40:00.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can I say this? Wealths-es of our various eligible guests.\N{\rCHT}可以叫貴客？他們身價有多少{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.14,0:40:02.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,And did she have any other specifications?\N{\rCHT}她有沒有指定其他條件？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.56,0:40:05.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Objection, Your Honor. Inflammatory. - What's good for the gander, Your Honor.\N{\rCHT}- 反對 煽動性 - 對男方有好處{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.02,0:40:08.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is this a legal argument. "What's good for the gander"?\N{\rCHT}"對男方有好處"是法律爭辨嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.32,0:40:09.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,You got to play your tape, Freddy.\N{\rCHT}我也讓你播出錄影帶啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.49,0:40:12.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Massey has a point there. I'm going to allow it.\N{\rCHT}梅西先生有道理 我批准{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.45,0:40:15.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Were there any other specifications?\N{\rCHT}還有沒有指定其他條件？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.12,0:40:18.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,She specificated a silly man.\N{\rCHT}她指定要個凱子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.16,0:40:20.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Objection, Your Honor! I'm going to allow it.\N{\rCHT}- 反對 - 批准{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.62,0:40:24.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,She specificated a man who, though clever at making money,\N{\rCHT}她指定要一個很會賺錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.33,0:40:26.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,would be easily duped and controlled.\N{\rCHT}卻又易受騙和擺佈的男人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.04,0:40:29.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Objection, Your Honor. - Shut up, Freddy. She's allowing it.\N{\rCHT}- 反對 - 閉嘴 佛萊迪 她會批准{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.34,0:40:33.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,She specificated a man with a wandering pee-pee.\N{\rCHT}她指定要一個好色鬼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.18,0:40:37.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,How you say? A philanderer whose affairs would be transparent to the world.\N{\rCHT}一個喜歡拈花惹草的 好色之徒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.68,0:40:38.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Objection, Your Honor!\N{\rCHT}反對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.76,0:40:43.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Finally, a man whom she could herself brazenly cuckold\N{\rCHT}她卻可以百無禁忌地通姦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.52,0:40:45.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,until such time as she might choose to...\N{\rCHT}直到她有機可乘…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.06,0:40:48.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,We would say, "Faire un coup de marteau sur des fesses."\N{\rCHT}我們說 "捉姦在床"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.73,0:40:51.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,You would say, "Make hammer on his fanny."\N{\rCHT}你們會說 "逮個正著"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.74,0:40:55.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Your Honor, objection! lrrelevant! - I'm going to allow it!\N{\rCHT}- 反對 無關 - 我批准{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.36,0:40:58.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell us, Baron, did you introduce her to such a man?\N{\rCHT}男爵 你有沒有介紹這樣的男人？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.37,0:41:00.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sir, I am the concierge!\N{\rCHT}我是客戶服務員嘛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.62,0:41:03.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,And to whom did you introduce that calculating woman?\N{\rCHT}你介紹誰給那位處心積慮的女士？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.37,0:41:07.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,I introduced her to that silly man.\N{\rCHT}我介紹給她那個凱子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.54,0:41:10.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your Honor, objection!\N{\rCHT}反對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.13,0:41:14.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let the record show that the Baron has identified Rex Rexroth as the silly man!\N{\rCHT}請記錄在案 男爵把雷克斯雷克諾斯稱為凱子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.22,0:41:18.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,I did it! It was I! I introduced her to that silly man!\N{\rCHT}是我介紹那個凱子給她的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.60,0:41:19.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,You son of a bitch!\N{\rCHT}混帳{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.76,0:41:22.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,The red-faced angry one. I introduced them!\N{\rCHT}我就是介紹這個氣得滿面通紅的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.93,0:41:26.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Absolutely! I did it! It was l!\N{\rCHT}沒錯 我是媒人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.19,0:41:29.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I just love trains! I love trains! - If you please, sir!\N{\rCHT}- 我只是喜歡火車 - 麻煩冷靜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.57,0:41:34.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not sick! You're the one who's sick!\N{\rCHT}變態的是你 不是我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.24,0:41:38.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you please, sir, not the larynx!\N{\rCHT}拜託不要掐脖子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.66,0:41:41.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Objection, Your Honor! Strangling the witness!\N{\rCHT}反對 勒殺證人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.20,0:41:43.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm going to allow it.\N{\rCHT}我批准{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.83,0:41:49.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I think it stinks. They left you with nothing.\N{\rCHT}他們太沒良心了 一分錢都不給你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.75,0:41:52.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Makes you wonder about the entire legal system,\N{\rCHT}司法制度太黑暗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.76,0:41:55.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,like Rodney what's-his-name.\N{\rCHT}員警甚至向黑人動私刑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.22,0:41:57.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,They bought Massey's argument.\N{\rCHT}他們贊同梅西說的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.18,0:42:00.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I lied and cheated and was with Rex only for his money,\N{\rCHT}我既然為錢才嫁雷克斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.10,0:42:01.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,then he shouldn't have to give me any.\N{\rCHT}就不應該得到分文{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.60,0:42:05.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that makes no sense. Why else would you put in all those years?\N{\rCHT}嫁人不是為錢 是為了什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.10,0:42:10.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Are you all right, Sarah? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 莎拉 你沒事吧？- 沒事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.61,0:42:14.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,What is it? Peptic ulcer.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼病？- 胃潰瘍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.28,0:42:18.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have medication, but I can't take it before elective surgery.\N{\rCHT}我有藥 但因為要整容 暫時不能吃藥{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.45,0:42:22.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be living here alone, Sarah.\N{\rCHT}莎拉 你不應該獨居{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.32,0:42:24.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,My goddamn husbands gave me the ulcer.\N{\rCHT}我那幾個前夫弄得我胃潰瘍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.58,0:42:27.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,But a bottle of Bromo can't love you back.\N{\rCHT}但制酸劑不會給你愛情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.54,0:42:31.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's a catch-22.\N{\rCHT}所以我現在進退兩難{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.29,0:42:37.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have to admit, I don't like living alone. I mean, do I need 46 rooms?\N{\rCHT}不可否認 我不喜歡獨居 我用得著46間房的大宅嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.22,0:42:40.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You could see people. - It's risky. Palimony.\N{\rCHT}- 你可以交男友 - 太冒險 贍養費{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.80,0:42:44.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch Marvin Mitchelson.\N{\rCHT}即使同居分手也要付生活費{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.10,0:42:49.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, honey, getting laid is financial Russian roulette.\N{\rCHT}玩男人隨時被男人反刮一筆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.14,0:42:53.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should just tear it all down, build a cottage.\N{\rCHT}也許我應該拆掉大宅 改建別墅{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.65,0:42:55.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,More landscaping.\N{\rCHT}多加添園景{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.20,0:43:02.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, with my money, I can't afford to be fooling around.\N{\rCHT}我有那麼多錢 不能勾三搭四{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.83,0:43:05.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,And besides, I have you. It'll be fun, just the girls.\N{\rCHT}幸好有你陪 我們女人自己享樂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.83,0:43:10.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, thanks, Sarah, but I can't sleep on your couch forever.\N{\rCHT}謝謝好意 莎拉 不過我不能永久寄住你家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.38,0:43:15.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm going to marry again, nail the guy's ass good.\N{\rCHT}我要嫁人 繼續捉姦在床{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.05,0:43:20.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,And this time, there'll be no Puffy von Espy.\N{\rCHT}不過 這次不用馮艾斯比拉皮條{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.36,0:43:37.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Knock, knock. Excuse me. Mr. Donaly?\N{\rCHT}你好 唐諾裡先生？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.40,0:43:39.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Donaly?\N{\rCHT}唐諾裡先生？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.07,0:43:41.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Donaly, excuse me.\N{\rCHT}唐諾裡先生 不好意思{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.53,0:43:46.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You are Donovan Donaly? - I'm in a meeting.\N{\rCHT}- 你是不是唐納文唐諾裡？- 我在開會{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.58,0:43:49.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Donaly. I need a name.\N{\rCHT}唐諾裡先生 我需要一個名字{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.09,0:43:58.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,And of course, we will have to litigate. Sentence, paragraph.\N{\rCHT}當然 我們要訴訟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.17,0:44:00.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Naturally,\N{\rCHT}當然{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.91,0:44:05.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,the first concern for both parties is the welfare of little Wendell Junior.\N{\rCHT}第一段 雙方應該以小溫戴爾的福祉為重{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.43,0:44:08.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, we do question whether the continuing expenses\N{\rCHT}不過 我們慎重懷疑是否有必要{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.06,0:44:11.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,for his special ed classes are truly justified, given the great strides...\N{\rCHT}繼續支付他特殊教育費用…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.77,0:44:16.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Massey, the senior partner would like to see you.\N{\rCHT}梅西先生 老闆要見你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.69,0:44:20.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Herb wants to see me? - If you have a moment.\N{\rCHT}- 賀伯要見我？- 你有空的話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.42,0:44:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}《加州法律評論》{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.08,0:44:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}《爭論解答期刊》{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.63,0:44:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}《法律期刊》{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.34,0:44:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}《割腸後如何生活》{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.76,0:44:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}解除點滴的束縛 20種自然散步法{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.35,0:44:57.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fourteen summary judgments sought.\N{\rCHT}申請即決判決14次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.90,0:45:00.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thirteen granted.\N{\rCHT}批准了13次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.44,0:45:07.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eighteen movements to void for respondent's prejudice.\N{\rCHT}申請歧視被告無效18次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.12,0:45:08.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eighteen granted.\N{\rCHT}批准了18次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.95,0:45:12.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Twelve court days on the Rexroth case alone.\N{\rCHT}雷克諾斯案只出庭12天{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.46,0:45:19.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Three hundred and twenty billable hours paralegal services.\N{\rCHT}賺得律師助手費320個小時{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.96,0:45:26.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Six hundred and eighty billable at full attorney rate.\N{\rCHT}賺得律師費680小時{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.26,0:45:31.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eighty-five lunches charged.\N{\rCHT}客戶支付午餐85次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.66,0:45:52.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Counselor,\N{\rCHT}律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.37,0:45:58.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,you are the engine that drives this firm.\N{\rCHT}你是本律師樓的棟樑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.47,0:46:09.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Massey?\N{\rCHT}梅西先生？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.43,0:46:12.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please, no calls. I'm feeling a little fragile.\N{\rCHT}我精神有點恍惚 暫時不接電話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.97,0:46:15.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mr. Massey, but I felt certain you'd want to know.\N{\rCHT}不好意思 梅西先生 但我相信你會想知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.60,0:46:17.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin Rexroth wants to see you.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯想見你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.23,0:46:20.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin. When did she...\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 她什麼時候…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.19,0:46:21.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,She's here now.\N{\rCHT}她已經來了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.02,0:46:25.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is she armed? Give me a minute.\N{\rCHT}有沒有持槍？等一等{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.91,0:46:39.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin. How nice of you to...\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 歡迎…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.54,0:46:43.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, shame on you.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 你應該覺得慚愧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.88,0:46:47.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, what a lovely surprise.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 好一個驚喜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.01,0:46:52.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, what a...\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 好一個…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.06,0:46:56.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Who the hell are you? - Hello, Miles. So nice of you to see us.\N{\rCHT}- 你是誰？- 邁爾斯 謝謝你見我們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.23,0:47:03.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,May I introduce Howard D. Doyle of Doyle Oil.\N{\rCHT}容我介紹道爾石油的霍爾道爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.61,0:47:05.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm goddamn pleased to meet you.\N{\rCHT}久仰大名{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.61,0:47:08.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin here, she says you're the best. Says you're aces.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮非常欣賞你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.15,0:47:10.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you, Mr...\N{\rCHT}謝謝你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.91,0:47:15.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Any relation to John D. Doyle of Doyle Oil?\N{\rCHT}道爾石油的約翰道爾是你親戚？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.49,0:47:18.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, you must be talking about Grandpa John. My papa's John D., too.\N{\rCHT}那是我爺爺 我爸也是約翰道爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.91,0:47:21.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Deuce, we called him. You know, kind of the rebel of the family.\N{\rCHT}我們叫他二世 像是家族慣例{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.58,0:47:23.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,But they knocked off that whole John D. routine\N{\rCHT}可是他們在我身上{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.63,0:47:25.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,when they christened little old yours truly here.\N{\rCHT}停止了約翰道爾的慣例{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.38,0:47:27.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Grandpa nearly had a stroke.\N{\rCHT}爺爺氣得差點中風{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.59,0:47:30.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,He did have a stroke, but that was later, during the labor activity in '52.\N{\rCHT}他在之後的1952年工運 的確中過風{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.47,0:47:33.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,The government stepped in. They called it mediation.\N{\rCHT}後來政府插手 稱為調停{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.05,0:47:36.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,He called it incipient communism, you know, and of course,\N{\rCHT}爺爺認為是左派作怪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.88,0:47:38.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,that's when he had his stroke.\N{\rCHT}氣得中風{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.10,0:47:41.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Golly, the whole left side of his body is as useless as tits on a boar hog.\N{\rCHT}左半身完全殘廢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.44,0:47:43.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,He lingered in a vegetative state for years.\N{\rCHT}他幾年來都像植物人一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.12,0:47:44.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that is fascinating, Mr. Doyle.\N{\rCHT}道爾先生 真精彩的故事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.77,0:47:46.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What say we have a seat? - A seat?\N{\rCHT}- 坐一下好嗎？- 坐？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.73,0:47:50.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here Marylin's had me runnin' up and down Rodeo Drive all day long.\N{\rCHT}我陪瑪麗蓮購物購了整天{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.28,0:47:52.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Kind of hit-and-run shoppin', you know. Take no prisoners.\N{\rCHT}火速行軍 買完就走{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.03,0:47:56.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forced march kind of thing. My God, my dogs are barkin'.\N{\rCHT}什麼都不錯過 兩條腿酸得要命{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.20,0:47:57.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,We started out at this little old place\N{\rCHT}我們從威爾夏的一個老地方{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.91,0:47:59.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,- right off of Wilshire... - It's been quite a day.\N{\rCHT}- 開始買起… - 一天下來好累{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.62,0:48:00.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Had pewter things. - But anyway, Miles,\N{\rCHT}- 花了很多錢 - 邁爾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.91,0:48:06.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know you're busy, and you charge by the hour, so I'll get straight to the point.\N{\rCHT}我知道你是按時收費的大忙人 廢話少說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:09.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Howard D. and I are planning to marry.\N{\rCHT}霍爾和我打算結婚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.55,0:48:14.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well...\N{\rCHT}這…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.64,0:48:18.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose that congratulations are in order.\N{\rCHT}那我應該恭喜你們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.14,0:48:20.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you, Miles. You know, the urge to wedlock\N{\rCHT}謝謝 邁爾斯 以莊嚴儀式確認{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.48,0:48:24.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,and form a lasting monogamous bond sanctified by ritual, it's pert-near universal.\N{\rCHT}夫妻結合 是世人的普遍願望{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.90,0:48:26.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact,\N{\rCHT}貴業務和婚姻有關{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.75,0:48:28.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,it might be of some interest to you, being in a related business.\N{\rCHT}或者也有興趣知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.48,0:48:31.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Even your indigenous Americans, I believe it was your Cree, used to...\N{\rCHT}即使美洲原住民也…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.45,0:48:35.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Howard and I are here because I've learned through bitter experience\N{\rCHT}我和霍爾今天來是因為 我從痛苦教訓中知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.74,0:48:40.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,that when it comes to matrimony and law, you are the very best.\N{\rCHT}在婚姻法方面 你是首屈一指的律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.29,0:48:43.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,And as you are well aware, my previous marriage\N{\rCHT}你清楚知道 上次婚姻破裂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.00,0:48:48.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,ended in an unjustified stain upon my reputation.\N{\rCHT}我信譽蒙屈遭人非議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.50,0:48:54.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,My motives were impugned. I was slandered in court.\N{\rCHT}在庭上受盡誹謗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.13,0:48:56.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was painted a harlot.\N{\rCHT}被指出賣色相{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.51,0:49:00.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Oh, honey, you ain't no harlot. - Oh, yes, honey.\N{\rCHT}- 甜心 你不是啊 - 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.47,0:49:04.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,So it's my desire to remove any trace of suspicion\N{\rCHT}所以我打算釋除我的愛人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.98,0:49:08.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,from the mind of my dear Howard Doyle.\N{\rCHT}霍爾道爾一切的疑慮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.02,0:49:10.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, honey, come on, now.\N{\rCHT}沒有必要嘛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.86,0:49:12.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wish to execute a prenuptial agreement.\N{\rCHT}我想簽訂婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.03,0:49:16.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I'm dead-set against it. I mean, just anti the whole deal.\N{\rCHT}我非常反對 覺得太煞風景{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.57,0:49:20.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Howard's lawyers prefer it. I insist upon it.\N{\rCHT}霍爾的律師贊成 我又堅持簽訂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.41,0:49:24.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, damn lawyers. No offense to the present company or anything, you know.\N{\rCHT}律師都是胡說八道 我並不是指你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.33,0:49:29.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, is it my understanding that the Massey prenup has never been penetrated?\N{\rCHT}梅西婚前協定絕對牢不可破 對不對？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.17,0:49:30.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is correct.\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.50,0:49:34.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not to blow my own horn, but they devote an entire semester to it at Harvard Law.\N{\rCHT}不是我自誇 哈佛法律學院 也用作教學材料{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.38,0:49:36.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,They got a hell of a school up there. Ain't no doubt about it.\N{\rCHT}好有名氣的大學{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.55,0:49:38.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,We donated that Doyle building up there here a while back.\N{\rCHT}我家捐了一棟樓給他們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.81,0:49:43.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, I myself went to Texas A&M. I'm an Aggie.\N{\rCHT}我自己是德州農機大學畢業{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.27,0:49:45.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Business? - Tight end.\N{\rCHT}- 主修商科？- 橄欖球邊鋒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.89,0:49:48.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I had a fair amount of success against the split-T defense.\N{\rCHT}當對方後衛布下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.77,0:49:50.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, when they line up symmetrical thataway,\N{\rCHT}一字長蛇陣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.77,0:49:52.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,it allows me to buttonhook and, you know,\N{\rCHT}我有辦法突然轉身{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.57,0:49:54.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,do a down-and-in, and up-and-out and different things,\N{\rCHT}用盡各種方法進攻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.95,0:49:59.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,post pattern every now and then. Your tight ends don't generally run a post.\N{\rCHT}邊鋒通常不正面攻過去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.20,0:50:00.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,But if the QB calls it, hell, I'm ready.\N{\rCHT}不過只要四分衛有需要 我也辦得到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.08,0:50:02.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Interrupt for a second? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 打岔一下？- 是{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.45,0:50:07.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wanna make sure that you both understand what it is you're asking.\N{\rCHT}我想確定你們明白自己的要求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.37,0:50:11.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Massey prenup provides that in the event of a dissolution of the marriage,\N{\rCHT}根據梅西婚前協定 萬一離婚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.29,0:50:13.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,for any reason,\N{\rCHT}無論是什麼原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.13,0:50:17.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,both parties will leave it with what they brought in and earned during.\N{\rCHT}雙方只可以 取回自己的財產{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.47,0:50:20.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one can profit from the marriage.\N{\rCHT}誰也不能獲益{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.97,0:50:23.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,The prenup protects the wealthier party.\N{\rCHT}協議保障較富有的一方{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.64,0:50:28.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Without it, that party is exposed, a sitting duck.\N{\rCHT}沒有協議 該方就沒有防衛力 任人宰割{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.69,0:50:34.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Not a hell of a lot of romance in that. - No, sir, there is not. No romance.\N{\rCHT}- 不浪漫 - 不浪漫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.36,0:50:36.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,More to the point, no wriggle room.\N{\rCHT}更重要的是 不留轉環餘地{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.95,0:50:42.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,So are we sure that this is what we want?\N{\rCHT}你們真的要簽訂這協議？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.79,0:50:46.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.\N{\rCHT}絕對要{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.41,0:50:51.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's my gift to Howard for his peace of mind.\N{\rCHT}不管霍爾擔不擔心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.13,0:50:55.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whether or not he's worried about it at this moment.\N{\rCHT}這是我送給他的定心丸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.96,0:50:58.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, honey pie, do I look worried?\N{\rCHT}甜心 我看起來擔心嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.01,0:51:04.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Mr. Doyle.\N{\rCHT}道爾先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.26,0:51:07.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Could I just borrow your charming fiancée for a moment?\N{\rCHT}可不可以把你的未婚嬌妻借我一下？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.52,0:51:10.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, okay. You gonna leave a deposit?\N{\rCHT}可以 你會不會留押金？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.78,0:51:18.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you up to?\N{\rCHT}你在打什麼主意？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.03,0:51:23.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Something you won't understand, Miles. Howard and I are very much in love.\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 你不會明白 霍爾和我心心相印{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.74,0:51:26.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're thinking, but I have to warn you,\N{\rCHT}我不知道你在想什麼 可是我得警告你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.20,0:51:28.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,the Massey prenup has never been penetrated.\N{\rCHT}我的梅西婚前協定是金鐘罩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.87,0:51:32.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,You sign the prenup, you can't get his money.\N{\rCHT}你簽名 就得不到他的錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.58,0:51:34.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the professional help.\N{\rCHT}謝謝你的專業幫忙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.59,0:51:40.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, think of me for a moment, not as an attorney but as a friend.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 暫時不要把我當律師 當我是朋友吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.80,0:51:43.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you won't be charging us for the hour?\N{\rCHT}你不收我們的律師費？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.68,0:51:46.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dump him. You can't nail his ass.\N{\rCHT}甩了他 你捉不到他的痛腳{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.27,0:51:50.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that all?\N{\rCHT}你說完了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.35,0:51:54.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, that's not all.\N{\rCHT}還沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.67,0:52:14.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,I could have you disbarred for that.\N{\rCHT}我可以令你吊銷執照{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.88,0:52:16.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,It was worth it.\N{\rCHT}值得冒那個險{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.76,0:52:20.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,A romantic divorce attorney.\N{\rCHT}浪漫的離婚律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.60,0:52:28.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,You fascinate me.\N{\rCHT}我為你著迷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.73,0:52:40.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll get right on it. I'll whip something up.\N{\rCHT}我會準備份講稿{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.65,0:52:42.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.45,0:52:46.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How's Lionel? - He's fine.\N{\rCHT}- 萊諾怎麼樣？- 很好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.66,0:52:51.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,He asked me to deliver the keynote address at this year's convention in Vegas.\N{\rCHT}賭城開律師大會 他請我發表揭幕演講{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.79,0:52:54.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That's quite an honor. - I suppose.\N{\rCHT}- 那是很高的榮譽 - 大概是吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.17,0:52:57.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,- On top of a great victory. - What was that?\N{\rCHT}- 加上你打贏了漂亮的一仗 - 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.20,0:53:00.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,"What was that"? Rex Rexroth?\N{\rCHT}"什麼"？雷克斯雷克諾斯？反對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.51,0:53:04.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,He kept everything? You win? No compromise? Isn't that what you wanted?\N{\rCHT}雷克斯保留全副資產 你還不滿意？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.60,0:53:10.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, good God, Miles. What are you looking for?\N{\rCHT}天啊 邁爾斯 你想怎樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.10,0:53:13.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\N{\rCHT}不知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.10,0:53:17.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, I won.\N{\rCHT}好 我打贏官司{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.15,0:53:21.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,What then?\N{\rCHT}那又怎樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.36,0:53:24.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,How many cases has Herb Myerson won?\N{\rCHT}賀伯邁爾森打贏多少起官司？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.11,0:53:26.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,The old man? More than anybody. He's a legend.\N{\rCHT}老頭子？比任何人多 他是傳奇人物{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.45,0:53:28.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,And look at him. He's 87 years old.\N{\rCHT}看他吧 87歲了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.08,0:53:32.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's the first one into the office in the morning. No home life.\N{\rCHT}大清早率先來律師樓 沒有家庭溫暖{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.95,0:53:34.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who needs a home when you have a colostomy bag?\N{\rCHT}當你掛著個便袋 誰需要家庭？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.79,0:53:37.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,She can't really love this dope, can she?\N{\rCHT}她不可能愛上那男人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.58,0:53:41.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Who? Who loves who? - Marylin Rexroth.\N{\rCHT}- 誰不可能愛上誰？- 瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.25,0:53:45.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,She signed a prenup for an oil millionaire.\N{\rCHT}她和一個石油富豪簽訂婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.30,0:53:49.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,A Massey prenup?\N{\rCHT}梅西婚前協議？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.06,0:53:56.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. - Well, then she is not after his money.\N{\rCHT}- 對 - 那麼她要的不是對方的錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.44,0:54:02.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Only love is in mind if the Massey is signed.\N{\rCHT}簽梅西協議 必定真情真意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.37,0:54:18.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ April, come she will ∮\N{\rCHT}四月 到來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.17,0:54:24.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ When streams are ripe and swelled with rain ∮\N{\rCHT}雨季來臨 溪水流淌{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.34,0:54:28.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ May, she will stay ∮\N{\rCHT}五月 停下腳步{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.89,0:54:34.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ Resting in my arms again ∮\N{\rCHT}在我懷中休息{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.53,0:54:46.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,What the hell's wrong with you?\N{\rCHT}你搞什麼鬼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.82,0:54:52.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ April, come she will∮ \N{\rCHT}四月 到來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.04,0:55:00.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming to this celebration\N{\rCHT}感謝各位光臨見證{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.79,0:55:04.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,of the love between our two friends, Marylin and Howard.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮與霍爾永結同心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.05,0:55:07.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,In today's cynical world,\N{\rCHT}世態爾虞我詐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.22,0:55:13.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's so hard to take that great leap of faith aboard the ship of love and caring.\N{\rCHT}現在甚少人有堅定信念 毅然登上情義號這艘船{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.57,0:55:17.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,But today Marylin and Howard are taking that leap\N{\rCHT}不過 今日瑪麗蓮與霍爾 跨出那一大步{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.18,0:55:19.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,and telling us, their friends,\N{\rCHT}向我們展示{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.39,0:55:24.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,that they do believe, that they do have faith, that they do love.\N{\rCHT}他們真誠的愛情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.15,0:55:28.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you, Howard Drexler Doyle, take Marylin\N{\rCHT}霍爾道爾 你願不願意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.53,0:55:31.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,to be your shipmate on this journey through life,\N{\rCHT}與瑪麗蓮一生同舟共濟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.36,0:55:35.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,through gale and doldrum, seas choppy, wild, and calm?\N{\rCHT}無論一帆風順抑或波濤洶湧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.91,0:55:37.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do, Father Scott.\N{\rCHT}史考特神父 我願意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.00,0:55:42.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,And do you, Marylin Rexroth, take Howard to be your shipmate and companion\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯 你願不願意 與霍爾結伴同航{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.71,0:55:47.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,to ports of every clime, be it in first class or steerage?\N{\rCHT}遍訪各地港口 無論坐的是下等艙抑或頭等房？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.51,0:55:49.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,I do.\N{\rCHT}我願意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.84,0:55:52.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then, by the power vested in me by the State of California,\N{\rCHT}我現在按照加州授我之權{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.93,0:55:55.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,and as captain of the good ship Amore Veritas,\N{\rCHT}並以情義號船長身份{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.72,0:55:58.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,I now pronounce you man and wife.\N{\rCHT}宣佈你們結為夫婦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.12,0:56:20.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\N{\rCHT}你認為怎樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.96,0:56:24.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What are they, ladles? - Berry spoons.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼東西？長柄匙？- 莓果匙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.29,0:56:25.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Spoons? - Berry spoons.\N{\rCHT}- 湯匙？- 莓果匙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.79,0:56:28.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Everybody has spoons. - And nobody needs berry spoons.\N{\rCHT}- 每個人都需要湯匙 - 但不需要莓果匙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.55,0:56:30.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Everybody eats berries. - Who are you, Pollyanna?\N{\rCHT}- 每個人都吃莓果 - 你什麼都往好處想？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.97,0:56:33.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, everybody! Folks! Hey, y'all! Where'd you see them at?\N{\rCHT}- 各位 - 從哪裡買的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.84,0:56:36.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,A Martha Stewart catalog right next to the silver napkin rings?\N{\rCHT}居家雜誌裡的銀制紙巾環旁邊？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.47,0:56:38.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I need your attention for a minute. - Stadium-seat ass-warmers?\N{\rCHT}- 請注意 - 馬桶加溫器？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.97,0:56:42.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dear God, Wrigley, how many cockamamie personal possessions do we have to amass?\N{\rCHT}天啊 雷格利 究竟要買多少無聊的東西才夠？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.23,0:56:43.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles, why so angry?\N{\rCHT}你幹嘛生氣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.35,0:56:45.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, I know it's not common practice\N{\rCHT}結婚之日{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.56,0:56:49.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,for the groom to give his bride a gift on their wedding day.\N{\rCHT}新郎沒有送禮給新娘的習慣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.32,0:56:53.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,But ever since I met Marylin there, I can't seem to quit givin' her things.\N{\rCHT}不過自從認識瑪麗蓮後 我似乎送不住手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.41,0:56:58.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I don't wanna stop 'cause it feels so darn good!\N{\rCHT}而且愈送愈開心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.20,0:57:02.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Chow Sing, bring that barbecue sauce over here, little buddy.\N{\rCHT}周辛 把燒烤汁端過來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.83,0:57:04.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,There you go.\N{\rCHT}這就對了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.67,0:57:07.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Put that thing on my neck now.\N{\rCHT}替我圍上圍巾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.75,0:57:11.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, honey, it's like the padre said. I want love and trust between us.\N{\rCHT}神父說得對 我們需要互愛互信{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.80,0:57:14.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Love, and trust, and not a thing else.\N{\rCHT}愛情與信任 如此而已{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.51,0:57:17.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,And this here deed that I'm fixin' to perform.\N{\rCHT}這是我要做的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.56,0:57:22.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, honey, let me just...\N{\rCHT}甜心 讓我…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.02,0:57:27.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see this?\N{\rCHT}看到了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.82,0:57:40.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is for you, darling. This here is for you.\N{\rCHT}為你而吃 為你而吃{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.87,0:57:46.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,This here is for you, baby. Every last little speck of it.\N{\rCHT}為你而吃 甜心 一點都不剩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.62,0:57:51.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,I love you. I mean, I love you like a son of a bitch!\N{\rCHT}我愛你 我愛你愛得要命{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.38,0:57:56.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,I trust you!\N{\rCHT}我信任你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.30,0:57:58.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,- This here is for you, baby. - Brilliant!\N{\rCHT}- 為你而吃 - 精彩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.89,0:58:00.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Baby, this is for you.\N{\rCHT}為你而吃{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.72,0:58:02.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What is it? - I really love you.\N{\rCHT}- 那是什麼？- 我真的愛你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.77,0:58:04.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the prenup.\N{\rCHT}婚前協議書{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.23,0:58:09.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,I love her! I trust her!\N{\rCHT}我愛她 我信任她{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.19,0:58:10.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Ladies and gentlemen... - It's the prenup!\N{\rCHT}- 各位… - 那是婚前協議書{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.98,0:58:13.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I trust her! - Brilliant!\N{\rCHT}- 我信任她 - 精彩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.78,0:58:19.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,You look so beautiful.\N{\rCHT}你好漂亮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.53,0:58:23.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ladies, if you'll excuse us. We have to talk.\N{\rCHT}不好意思 我們要談談{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.62,0:58:29.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,I would like to offer my congratulations. It was a beautiful gesture of Howard's.\N{\rCHT}恭喜恭喜 霍爾做得瀟灑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.75,0:58:34.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, Howard is a beautiful person. A diamond in the rough.\N{\rCHT}霍爾是一顆未經琢磨的鑽石{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.80,0:58:37.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I have a feeling that someday soon,\N{\rCHT}大概很快{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.13,0:58:40.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,you'll be taking that diamond and leaving the rough.\N{\rCHT}你會摘下鑽石 讓他自己琢磨自己{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.43,0:58:44.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,In a month or so, once I've established that I've tried to make the marriage work.\N{\rCHT}一兩個月後吧 我要先顯示 對這段婚姻的誠意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.60,0:58:48.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,- May I offer my services? - Oh, thanks.\N{\rCHT}- 我可以為你效勞嗎？- 謝了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.60,0:58:52.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, no. No, I'm retaining Freddy Bender.\N{\rCHT}不過不用客氣 我會繼續聘用佛萊迪班德{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.23,0:58:54.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Poor Freddy. He was awfully blue after my last divorce.\N{\rCHT}我離婚以來 佛萊迪一直難過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.07,0:58:56.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I admire your loyalty.\N{\rCHT}你起碼對律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.82,0:58:58.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,To lawyers, anyway.\N{\rCHT}有情有義{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.95,0:59:02.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,I guess without the prenup, it's something that even Freddy could manage.\N{\rCHT}沒有婚前協議 連佛萊迪也處理得來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.16,0:59:07.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,But how did you get Howard to do it? It felt like it was his idea.\N{\rCHT}你是怎麼讓霍爾自願那樣做的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.12,0:59:09.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Surely, Mr. Massey, you've addressed enough juries\N{\rCHT}梅西先生 暗示手法{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:12.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,to appreciate the power of suggestion.\N{\rCHT}也是你經常對陪審團用的那招{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.76,0:59:21.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, now that the marriage is winding down,\N{\rCHT}你這段婚姻既然就快結束{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.22,0:59:24.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,have dinner with me.\N{\rCHT}和我吃頓晚飯吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.97,0:59:30.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,No. No, nothing doing until the ink is dry on the settlement.\N{\rCHT}離婚協議上的墨水幹透才算{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.40,0:59:34.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, this'll be no settlement. If I know Marylin Rexroth,\N{\rCHT}你不會妥協的 就我所知的瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.52,0:59:40.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,this'll be nothing short of a complete and total annihilation.\N{\rCHT}會把對方殺個片甲不留{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.87,0:59:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}六個月後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.09,1:00:01.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You're gonna win. - Excuse me?\N{\rCHT}- 你會贏 - 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.68,1:00:05.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can always tell, going to Vegas, who's gonna win.\N{\rCHT}誰去賭城會贏 我看得出來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.43,1:00:08.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, thanks, but I'm going on business.\N{\rCHT}謝謝 不過我是去出差{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.23,1:00:10.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,I always win.\N{\rCHT}我一向都贏{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.15,1:00:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}凱撒皇宮-六月八日星期六 凱撒皇宮歡迎婚姻法律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.15,1:00:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}全國婚姻法律師公會{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.95,1:00:29.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know why I hate this town, Wrigley? You see, people get to Las Vegas,\N{\rCHT}雷格利 知道我為什麼討厭賭城嗎？大家只要一來這裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.04,1:00:32.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden, the rules of the moral universe don't apply.\N{\rCHT}就完全不顧道德{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.04,1:00:35.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,When God is dead, all things are possible.\N{\rCHT}上帝已死 肆無忌憚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.59,1:00:37.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,I saw an ad in the paper,\N{\rCHT}報上有這樣的廣告{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.55,1:00:42.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,"No-fault divorce. Two-week divorce without a lawyer."\N{\rCHT}"無過錯離婚 無須律師 兩星期辦妥"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.84,1:00:46.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Made me sick to my stomach. "No-fault divorce."\N{\rCHT}令我反胃 "無過錯離婚"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.22,1:00:49.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good God. Talk about your oxymoron.\N{\rCHT}天啊 自相矛盾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.60,1:00:52.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What's the world coming to? - One man can only do so much.\N{\rCHT}- 世界變怎樣了？- 個人力量有限{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.44,1:00:55.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,One man... What are you talking about?\N{\rCHT}個人… 你在說什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.40,1:00:56.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy.\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.90,1:00:58.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mmm. I had lunch with Freddy Bender yesterday.\N{\rCHT}我昨天跟佛萊迪班德吃午餐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.65,1:01:02.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,He tells me that Marylin Rexroth-Doyle is now richer than Croesus.\N{\rCHT}他說瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯道爾 現在比富翁還有錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.11,1:01:05.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes, but is she richer than Mrs. Croesus?\N{\rCHT}不過會不會比富翁太太有錢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.53,1:01:08.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,She could buy and sell you 10 times over.\N{\rCHT}她比你有錢十倍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.16,1:01:12.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,My God, is that her?\N{\rCHT}天啊 那是她嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.58,1:01:17.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy said she was flying in with him. Celebrating, I guess.\N{\rCHT}她和佛萊迪一起來 大概是來慶祝的吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.25,1:01:20.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm fascinated by that creature. Richer than me, huh?\N{\rCHT}魅力擋不住 比我有錢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.84,1:01:25.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, she deserves every penny. And now she's single again.\N{\rCHT}那是她應得的 現在她又單身了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.59,1:01:28.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.\N{\rCHT}失陪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.43,1:01:30.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, you should stay away from her, Miles.\N{\rCHT}不要去招惹她 邁爾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.85,1:01:33.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Recite your keynote address. Take a cold shower.\N{\rCHT}去練習講詞吧 沖個冷水澡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.03,1:01:44.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You're looking well, Marylin. - Hello, Miles.\N{\rCHT}- 你明豔照人啊 瑪麗蓮 - 你好 邁爾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.82,1:01:48.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Obscene wealth becomes you.\N{\rCHT}銅臭味很配你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.28,1:01:51.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I should've known you'd be here. - Be here?\N{\rCHT}- 我早該知道你會在這 - 在這？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.79,1:01:54.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm the keynote speaker. - How nice for you.\N{\rCHT}- 我是主演講人 - 真好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.75,1:01:57.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- "Nailing Your Spouse's Assets." - Excuse me?\N{\rCHT}- "緊抓配偶的資產" - 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.96,1:01:59.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,My speech.\N{\rCHT}我的講詞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.30,1:02:06.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Oh, I'm sure you'll bring the house down. - It's an easy crowd.\N{\rCHT}- 必定會大受歡迎 - 好學的聽眾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.38,1:02:09.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,At this point, I would think you're probably the only person\N{\rCHT}但你大概是唯一一個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.47,1:02:12.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- that I can't teach anything to. - Really?\N{\rCHT}- 不用我教的人了 - 真的嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.85,1:02:18.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, correct me, but since by now the ink must be dry,\N{\rCHT}沒有說錯的話 現在既然墨水已經幹了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.19,1:02:21.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I believe I have the right to collect. - On?\N{\rCHT}- 你要履行承諾 - 什麼承諾？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.69,1:02:24.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,You promised to have dinner with me once you were free.\N{\rCHT}你答應恢復自由身後陪我吃飯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.03,1:02:29.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,I said I wouldn't whilst I wasn't, which implies no promise once I am.\N{\rCHT}我說我還沒自由不能陪你 我沒有說自由就陪你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.20,1:02:31.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Noted. Let me rephrase.\N{\rCHT}明白 讓我改問一句{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.87,1:02:36.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,I would be delighted, honored really, if you'd...\N{\rCHT}你肯不肯賞臉…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.00,1:02:39.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Howard! - Howard!\N{\rCHT}- 霍爾 - 霍爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.92,1:02:41.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Howard!\N{\rCHT}霍爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.67,1:02:46.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You named him after your ex. - I'm sentimental.\N{\rCHT}- 你用前夫的名字做狗名 - 我念舊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.80,1:02:52.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm free this evening, so I suppose a little dinner would do no harm.\N{\rCHT}我今晚有空 吃頓飯大概無傷大雅{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.93,1:02:56.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Le Veuve Clicquot Ponsardin 1990, sir.\N{\rCHT}1990年凱歌皇牌特級香檳{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.27,1:02:59.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you. I'll take care of it.\N{\rCHT}謝謝 我自己倒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.52,1:03:05.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, this is a moment to savor.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 這是值得回味的一刻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.86,1:03:10.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, we were adversaries, but we were also professionals.\N{\rCHT}你我不打不相識 識英雄頌英雄{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.20,1:03:16.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,So let us raise a glass to friendship.\N{\rCHT}為我們的友誼舉杯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.42,1:03:20.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,To victory.\N{\rCHT}敬勝利{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.88,1:03:29.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,So how does it feel?\N{\rCHT}有什麼感覺？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.76,1:03:33.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Sorry? - Victory. Independence.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼？- 勝利 獨立{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.06,1:03:41.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well, frankly, Miles... - It's not everything you'd hoped for?\N{\rCHT}- 老實說 邁爾斯… - 不盡如你理想吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.48,1:03:47.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know the feeling.\N{\rCHT}我明白那感受{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.32,1:03:52.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Independence. Two-edged sword.\N{\rCHT}獨立是雙面刃{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.66,1:03:57.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,My friend... My best friend, Sarah Sorkin.\N{\rCHT}我的知己莎拉索金{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.25,1:04:02.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sarah Battista-O'Flanagan-Sorkin?\N{\rCHT}莎拉巴提斯達奧法納根索金？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.38,1:04:05.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,The O'Flanagan settlement?\N{\rCHT}有名的奧法納根離婚協議？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.26,1:04:13.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, three fine settlements.\N{\rCHT}經過三次成功離婚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.76,1:04:16.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,More money than she could ever hope to spend.\N{\rCHT}她的錢多得花之不盡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.22,1:04:18.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes. - Her vaunted independence.\N{\rCHT}- 對 - 她自詡獨立{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.52,1:04:21.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me. She sits around the house,\N{\rCHT}讓我猜 她卻獨坐家中{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.27,1:04:23.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,afraid to see people, afraid to put her portfolio into play.\N{\rCHT}怕見人 怕花錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.06,1:04:28.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,And only a peptic ulcer to keep her warm at night.\N{\rCHT}晚上和胃潰瘍相依為命{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.53,1:04:29.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.28,1:04:35.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's a certain point when you've achieved your goals.\N{\rCHT}目的即使達到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.49,1:04:39.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,You realize that you're still not satisfied.\N{\rCHT}卻只剩下惆悵{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.54,1:04:40.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.88,1:04:49.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,We should order.\N{\rCHT}我們應該點菜了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.01,1:04:55.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm not really hungry.\N{\rCHT}其實我並不餓{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.47,1:04:57.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Neither am l.\N{\rCHT}我也不餓{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.35,1:05:44.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eighteen hundred billable hours.\N{\rCHT}賺得律師費1800小時{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.81,1:05:48.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,Twelve hundred twenty-one motions to void.\N{\rCHT}婚約無效1221次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.52,1:05:54.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Five hundred and sixty-four summary judgments.\N{\rCHT}即決判決564次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.20,1:05:58.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,A hundred and twenty-nine thousand\N{\rCHT}129999次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.03,1:06:03.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,nine hundred and ninety-nine lunches charged.\N{\rCHT}收費午餐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.68,1:06:24.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hello? - Miles?\N{\rCHT}- 喂？- 邁爾斯？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.14,1:06:26.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello? Marylin?\N{\rCHT}喂？瑪麗蓮？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.44,1:06:28.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sarah Sorkin just died!\N{\rCHT}莎拉索金剛剛去世了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.69,1:06:34.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Marylin! - Her ulcer.\N{\rCHT}- 瑪麗蓮 - 她的胃潰瘍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.86,1:06:41.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Perforated. Infection. - Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 胃穿孔 感染 - 是{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.37,1:06:47.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Miles? - Yes, Marylin?\N{\rCHT}- 邁爾斯？- 瑪麗蓮？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.50,1:06:49.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,She was alone.\N{\rCHT}她死時是一個人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.96,1:06:54.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,She'd been dead for two days before her Pilates instructor found her.\N{\rCHT}死了兩天才被人發現{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.97,1:07:02.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, listen to me. No arguments. No discussions.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 聽我說 不要猶疑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.26,1:07:04.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll have Wrigley meet us at the Wee Kirk o' the Heather.\N{\rCHT}我叫雷格利在幸運花教堂等我們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.37,1:07:11.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wrigley!\N{\rCHT}雷格利{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.31,1:07:13.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,The vows are from an Arapaho dawn-greeting ceremony.\N{\rCHT}誓詞來自印地安人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.23,1:07:17.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,The music is Simon & Garfunkel. And this is the Massey prenup.\N{\rCHT}音樂來自賽門與葛芬柯 這是梅西婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.11,1:07:21.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You the two getting married? - Mr. MacKinnon here will be officiating.\N{\rCHT}- 你們要結婚？- 麥金諾先生主婚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.07,1:07:24.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Sorry. Short notice. - Pen.\N{\rCHT}- 抱歉 倉促通知 - 筆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.54,1:07:28.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, you're welcome to examine this.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 隨便看 不要客氣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.08,1:07:31.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is the Massey prenup.\N{\rCHT}這是梅西婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.83,1:07:34.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,As you know, it's ironclad.\N{\rCHT}一如你所知 絕對保險{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.88,1:07:37.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,We tried to reach Freddy Bender to have him here for your protection,\N{\rCHT}我們找過佛萊迪班德來維持你的權利{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.48,1:07:38.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,but we couldn't find him.\N{\rCHT}不過找不到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.53,1:07:41.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you two here to get married or to bullshit?\N{\rCHT}你們是來結婚還是來講廢話的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.34,1:07:44.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you can't hope to benefit from the marriage?\N{\rCHT}所以你不能夠從婚姻中獲益？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.22,1:07:45.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not in any way.\N{\rCHT}絕對不能{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.81,1:07:49.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,And my wealth is completely, completely protected?\N{\rCHT}我的資產完全受到保障？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.19,1:07:52.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,As if a lead veil had been drawn across it.\N{\rCHT}就像裝上銅牆鐵壁一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.95,1:08:04.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you still want to marry me? - More than ever.\N{\rCHT}- 你仍然願意娶我？- 心甘情願{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.50,1:08:09.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you renting kilts?\N{\rCHT}你要不要租蘇格蘭裙？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.47,1:08:30.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you, Miles Longfellow Massey\N{\rCHT}梅西邁爾森律師事務所的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.77,1:08:35.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,of Massey, Myerson, Sloan and Gurolnick, LLP,\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯朗費羅梅西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.27,1:08:40.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,take Marylin Hamilton-Rexroth-Doyle to be your lawful wedded wife?\N{\rCHT}你願不願意娶瑪麗蓮漢密爾頓 雷克諾斯道爾為妻？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.78,1:08:42.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,I do. Yes. I do. I do.\N{\rCHT}我願意 我願意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.82,1:08:47.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me finish. Jesus, have you never been married before?\N{\rCHT}等我說完 難道你沒結過婚嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.08,1:08:52.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,To have and to hold, to love and to cherish, till death do you part?\N{\rCHT}互相扶持 相親相愛 至死方分？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.71,1:08:56.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I do.\N{\rCHT}我願意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.04,1:09:01.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,And do you, Marylin Hamilton-Rexroth-Doyle,\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮漢密爾頓雷克諾斯道爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.22,1:09:05.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,take Miles Longfellow Massey to be your lawful wedded husband,\N{\rCHT}你願不願意 嫁邁爾斯朗費羅梅西為夫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.22,1:09:10.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,to have and to hold, to love and to cherish, till death do you part?\N{\rCHT}互相扶持 相親相愛 至死方分？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.43,1:09:14.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I do. - I now pronounce you man and wife.\N{\rCHT}- 我願意 - 現在宣佈你們結為夫婦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.22,1:09:49.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of you later.\N{\rCHT}等一下再給你小費{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.11,1:10:03.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no, no. No. This is all wrong.\N{\rCHT}不 不 不 這樣不對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.61,1:10:07.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is it the kilt?\N{\rCHT}因為蘇格蘭裙？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.62,1:10:11.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you love me? - More than anything.\N{\rCHT}- 你愛我嗎？- 勝過一切{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.91,1:10:17.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Can I trust you? - Yes, you can trust me.\N{\rCHT}- 我能信任你嗎？- 你能信任我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.93,1:10:28.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Darling, you're exposed.\N{\rCHT}你沒有防衛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.51,1:10:30.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,A sitting duck.\N{\rCHT}任人宰割{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.16,1:10:50.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,I hereby declare the 12th Congress\N{\rCHT}謹宣佈第12屆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.08,1:10:56.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,of the National Organization of MatrimoniaI Attorneys Nationwide open.\N{\rCHT}全國婚姻法律律師大會開幕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.71,1:10:58.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,As our first order of business,\N{\rCHT}首先{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.50,1:11:02.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,it is a privilege to call to the podium our keynote speaker.\N{\rCHT}我們萬分榮幸 有請主演講人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.38,1:11:07.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,From the Los Angeles firm of Massey, Myerson, Sloan and Gurolnick,\N{\rCHT}洛杉磯梅西邁爾森律師事務所的律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.26,1:11:12.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,a man whose name is synonymous with bitter disputes and big awards,\N{\rCHT}以辦理激烈離婚 爭取高額補償而大名鼎鼎的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.01,1:11:14.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles Massey.\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯梅西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.57,1:11:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}全國婚姻法律師公會 "讓我們分離"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.16,1:11:34.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Branco.\N{\rCHT}謝謝你 布蘭科{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.87,1:11:40.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the world of...\N{\rCHT}婚姻法…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.34,1:11:47.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the world of matrimonial law, there are...\N{\rCHT}婚姻法的世界…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.47,1:11:59.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the world of matrimonial law, there are multiple tactics.\N{\rCHT}婚姻法的世界裡 有不同戰略{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.74,1:12:18.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Friends,\N{\rCHT}各位朋友{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.08,1:12:24.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,this morning I stand before you a very different Miles Massey\N{\rCHT}今天的邁爾斯梅西 和去年的邁爾斯梅西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.17,1:12:26.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,than the one that addressed you last year\N{\rCHT}是兩個不同的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.84,1:12:30.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,on the disposition of marital assets following murder/suicide.\N{\rCHT}去年我發表 夫婦同歸於盡後如何分產{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.72,1:12:34.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wish to talk to you today not about technical matters of law.\N{\rCHT}我現在想講的不是法律技術{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.81,1:12:40.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wish to talk to you about something more important.\N{\rCHT}我想講更重要的事情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.23,1:12:45.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wish to talk to you from the heart.\N{\rCHT}我想向各位吐露肺府之言{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.11,1:12:55.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because today, for the first time in my life,\N{\rCHT}因為今天 我人生中第一次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.08,1:13:00.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,I stand before you naked,\N{\rCHT}我赤裸裸地站在{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.71,1:13:06.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,vulnerable,\N{\rCHT}各位面前{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.13,1:13:13.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,and in love.\N{\rCHT}而且在戀愛中{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.31,1:13:21.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Love.\N{\rCHT}愛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.35,1:13:25.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a word we matrimonial lawyers avoid.\N{\rCHT}我們婚姻律師避免的字眼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.36,1:13:29.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Funny, isn't it? We're frightened of this emotion,\N{\rCHT}奇怪吧？有愛才有婚姻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.98,1:13:34.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is, in a sense, the seed of our livelihood.\N{\rCHT}我們婚姻律師卻害怕愛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.49,1:13:41.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, today Miles Massey is here to tell you that love need cause us no fear.\N{\rCHT}今天我邁爾斯梅西要告訴各位 愛並不可怕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.25,1:13:48.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Love need cause us no shame. Love is...\N{\rCHT}愛並不羞愧 愛是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.17,1:13:51.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good.\N{\rCHT}善{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.18,1:13:58.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Love is good.\N{\rCHT}愛是善{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.43,1:14:04.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now I am, of course, aware\N{\rCHT}這樣說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.89,1:14:08.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,that these remarks will be received here with cynicism.\N{\rCHT}必然會引來冷嘲熱諷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.69,1:14:13.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cynicism, that cloak that advertises our indifference\N{\rCHT}我們以輕蔑的態度{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.32,1:14:15.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,and hides all human feeling.\N{\rCHT}來掩飾自己的感情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.61,1:14:19.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm here to tell you that that cynicism which we think protects us,\N{\rCHT}我們以為在保護自己的譏笑{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.16,1:14:21.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,in fact, destroys.\N{\rCHT}歧視是毀滅{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.95,1:14:27.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Destroys love, destroys our clients, and, ultimately, destroys ourselves.\N{\rCHT}摧毀愛 摧毀我們的當事人 最終摧毀我們自己{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.75,1:14:33.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Colleagues, when our clients come to us confused and angry and hurting\N{\rCHT}當客戶來找我們 又彷徨又憤怒又傷心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.51,1:14:37.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,because their flame of love is guttering and threatens to die,\N{\rCHT}他們愛的火焰明滅不定{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.26,1:14:39.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,do we seek to extinguish that flame\N{\rCHT}我們應該熄滅火焰{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.64,1:14:43.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,so that we can sift through the smoldering wreckage for our paltry reward?\N{\rCHT}好在灰燼中找尋利益？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.56,1:14:46.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Or do we fan this precious flame,\N{\rCHT}還是應該煽亮 這彌足可貴的火種{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.39,1:14:51.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,this most precious flame, back into loving, roaring life?\N{\rCHT}以期回覆熾熱的生命？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.44,1:14:57.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do we counsel fear or trust? Do we seek to destroy or build?\N{\rCHT}我們該鼓吹猜疑還是信任？我們該尋求破壞還是建設？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.91,1:15:02.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do we meet our clients' problems with cynicism\N{\rCHT}對當事人的煩惱我們該嗤之以鼻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.45,1:15:05.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,or with love?\N{\rCHT}還是體諒關懷？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.59,1:15:14.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,The choice is, of course, each of ours.\N{\rCHT}各有各的選擇{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.42,1:15:21.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,For my part, I've made the leap of love, and there's no going back.\N{\rCHT}我決意投入愛的陣營 義無反顧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.93,1:15:24.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, this is the last time I will address you\N{\rCHT}各位 這是我最後一次以會長{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.39,1:15:27.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,as the president of N.O.M.A.N. or as a member.\N{\rCHT}或會員的身份發表演講{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.94,1:15:35.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I intend to devote myself to pro bono work in East Los Angeles\N{\rCHT}我打算去洛杉磯東區等地{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.94,1:15:37.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,or one of those other...\N{\rCHT}做義務律師…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.91,1:15:44.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,God bless you all.\N{\rCHT}願神保佑你們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.88,1:16:35.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,I love you, man.\N{\rCHT}我愛你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.81,1:16:53.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, Wrigley, I'm gonna be relinquishing my partnership in Massey Myerson.\N{\rCHT}雷格利 我打算辭退律師事務所的工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.35,1:16:57.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you care to join me in my new endeavor, I'd be delighted.\N{\rCHT}歡迎你參與我的新嘗試{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.36,1:16:59.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course, I can't offer you the same kind of financial remuneration\N{\rCHT}我不能給你跟以前一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.99,1:17:01.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,you've grown accustomed to,\N{\rCHT}同樣的報酬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.11,1:17:02.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,but the work'll have to serve as its own reward.\N{\rCHT}但工作本身就是報酬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.90,1:17:05.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Barkeep, we'll have two of your finest scotches.\N{\rCHT}酒保 兩杯最好的威士卡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.87,1:17:08.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That's the... - I propose a toast.\N{\rCHT}- 那是… - 舉杯慶祝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.20,1:17:10.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Barkeep! - That's the soap that used to belong to...\N{\rCHT}- 酒保 - 那出肥皂劇本來是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.75,1:17:12.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll be serving in a junior capacity, of course.\N{\rCHT}只有低階的工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.00,1:17:14.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Donovan Donaly.\N{\rCHT}唐納文唐諾裡的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.58,1:17:16.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles, that's...\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 那…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.04,1:17:19.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,It'll be a small operation, a boutique firm.\N{\rCHT}我會開一間小型律師事務所{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.09,1:17:20.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you what they called me in medical school.\N{\rCHT}讓我告訴你我在醫學院裡的綽號{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.88,1:17:23.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,In any firm, there can be only one ramrod.\N{\rCHT}一間公司只能有一個主管{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.13,1:17:25.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't see why my leadership skills should...\N{\rCHT}以我的領導才能…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.76,1:17:27.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Howard? - Mackenzie the Mechanical Marvel.\N{\rCHT}- 霍爾？- 機器超人麥肯錫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.97,1:17:30.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's Howard. - You see, I have no nerves.\N{\rCHT}- 是霍爾 - 我沒有神經{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.14,1:17:33.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's not an oil tycoon. An actor.\N{\rCHT}他不是石油富豪 是演員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.15,1:17:37.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Doctor, this is highly unusual.\N{\rCHT}醫生 這非常不尋常{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.40,1:17:40.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,So Marylin married a soap actor.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮嫁給了肥皂劇演員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.86,1:17:45.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,So she's... She's poor.\N{\rCHT}那麼她… 她很窮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.41,1:17:48.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get yourself some clean scrubs, and have them prepare the OR.\N{\rCHT}換上手術袍 準備手術室{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.91,1:17:51.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well, thank God you have the prenup. - I have no prenup.\N{\rCHT}- 幸好你有婚前協議 - 我沒有婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.08,1:17:54.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You have no prenup. - I have no prenup.\N{\rCHT}- 你沒有婚前協議 - 我沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.71,1:17:56.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have no prenup.\N{\rCHT}你沒有婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.88,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3\fn華文楷體\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&}瑪麗蓮漢密爾頓雷克諾斯道爾梅西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.68,1:18:07.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\N{\rCHT}謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.35,1:18:11.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.94,1:18:18.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Marylin? - Oh, hello, Miles.\N{\rCHT}- 瑪麗蓮？- 邁爾斯 你好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.28,1:18:26.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Going back to LA? - Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 你要回洛杉磯？- 對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.20,1:18:31.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, Miles, I think it's only fair to warn you that after a decent interval,\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 經過一段合理時間{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.79,1:18:34.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,I intend to have Freddy seek an injunction\N{\rCHT}我會叫佛萊迪申請禁制令{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.45,1:18:37.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,that would forbid you to approach within 500 feet of my house.\N{\rCHT}禁止你在我房子150公尺範圍內出現{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.83,1:18:39.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You mean my house.\N{\rCHT}你指我的房子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.25,1:18:43.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, I believe the residence will be part of the settlement.\N{\rCHT}房子將會是協議的一部分{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.55,1:18:50.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, didn't last night mean anything to you?\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 昨晚對你完全沒有意義嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.43,1:18:54.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, about as much as it'll mean to you, half of your net worth.\N{\rCHT}和對你的意義一樣 你一半的身價{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.48,1:19:02.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles, you'll always be my favorite husband. But no more sentiment, darling.\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 你將會是我最喜愛的前夫 不必囉囉唆唆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.44,1:19:05.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,I really have to be going.\N{\rCHT}我真的要走了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.82,1:19:08.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,The dog's rented.\N{\rCHT}狗是租來的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.75,1:19:21.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You didn't win. - Excuse me?\N{\rCHT}- 你沒有贏 - 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.46,1:19:25.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can always tell, coming back from Vegas, who didn't win.\N{\rCHT}我從乘客的神情看得出來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.38,1:19:30.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're right.\N{\rCHT}你說得對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.93,1:19:40.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,But you're going through with it?\N{\rCHT}但是你決定離婚辦到底？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.48,1:19:42.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.56,1:19:46.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just felt so sorry for him for a minute there.\N{\rCHT}我一度為他難過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.36,1:19:49.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,At the preliminary hearing, he just looked so beaten.\N{\rCHT}預審時 他像鬥敗的公雞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.70,1:19:52.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well, he was beaten fair and square. - I know, but...\N{\rCHT}- 他應該輸得心服口服 - 我知道 可是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.70,1:19:54.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, their pathetic look.\N{\rCHT}裝可憐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.70,1:19:58.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's what they all fall back on when they don't have a prenup.\N{\rCHT}沒有婚前協議 他們唯有博取同情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.83,1:20:05.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just stay strong until the divorce is final.\N{\rCHT}你要堅強 一定要把離婚辦完{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.09,1:20:08.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Relax and enjoy your pool.\N{\rCHT}好好休養 享受泳池樂趣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.51,1:20:16.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you think he's eating enough? - Marylin!\N{\rCHT}- 他吃得好嗎？- 瑪麗蓮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.64,1:20:20.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,This woman has humbled,\N{\rCHT}此婦人把整間律師樓{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.44,1:20:26.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,shamed, and disgraced the entire firm.\N{\rCHT}打個落花流水 顏面無存{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.57,1:20:32.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes, Herb. - Counselor, this firm deals in power.\N{\rCHT}- 是 賀伯 - 律師 本律師樓講究實力{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.53,1:20:37.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,This firm deals in perception.\N{\rCHT}本律師樓講究洞察力{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.91,1:20:42.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,This firm cannot prosper, nor long endure\N{\rCHT}本律師樓當眾任人玩弄於股掌之間{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.00,1:20:49.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,if it is perceived to be dancing to the music of a hurdy-gurdy!\N{\rCHT}就再沒有江湖地位{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.42,1:20:52.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's just...\N{\rCHT}只是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.26,1:20:59.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Herb, for the first time in my career, I don't know what to do.\N{\rCHT}賀伯 我自出道以來 初次不知所措{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.77,1:21:05.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm a patsy. I'm a sitting duck. I'm lost.\N{\rCHT}我做了凱子 任人宰割 我失敗了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.44,1:21:07.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Lost?\N{\rCHT}失敗？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.19,1:21:11.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what you can do. You can act like a man.\N{\rCHT}我不想聽 男子漢大丈夫 我要你拿出氣概來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.20,1:21:14.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,And let me tell you something, smart guy.\N{\rCHT}你自作聰明{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.82,1:21:17.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,You thought you had it all figured out.\N{\rCHT}以為大徹大悟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.66,1:21:24.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Trust. Marriage. All your goddamn love, love, love!\N{\rCHT}說什麼信任 婚姻 什麼愛 愛 愛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.96,1:21:29.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, you listen to me. I'm gonna talk to you about the goddamn law.\N{\rCHT}聽著 讓我告訴你什麼是法律{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.96,1:21:33.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,We serve the law! We honor the law!\N{\rCHT}我們奉行法律 我們尊重法律{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.97,1:21:39.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,And sometimes, Counselor, we obey the law.\N{\rCHT}有時我們就是法律{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.06,1:21:46.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, Counselor, this is not one of those times.\N{\rCHT}不過現在不是守法的時候{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.03,1:22:00.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you Wheezy Joe?\N{\rCHT}你是不是氣喘喬？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.04,1:22:03.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which of you is Smith?\N{\rCHT}你們哪個是史密斯？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.71,1:22:09.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, we're here representing Mr. Smith on a matter of some delicacy.\N{\rCHT}我們是代表史密斯先生 來洽談某敏感事宜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.67,1:22:12.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Who's the pigeon? - The what?\N{\rCHT}- 誰是靶？- 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.13,1:22:15.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Who you want me to kill? - Yes. Well, we would like you...\N{\rCHT}- 要我殺誰？- 我們想…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.43,1:22:19.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Smith would like you to neutralize,\N{\rCHT}史密斯先生想麻煩你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.01,1:22:25.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,terminate, render unto a state of, so that she isn't so much...\N{\rCHT}廢掉她武功 使得她再不能夠…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.60,1:22:29.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Breathing. - Yes. A business associate\N{\rCHT}- 呼吸 - 對 她叫做{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.98,1:22:33.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,by the name of Marylin Rexroth-Doyle-Massey... Smith-Massey.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮雷克諾斯道爾梅西… 史密斯梅西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.78,1:22:37.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that one person?\N{\rCHT}是一個人嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.78,1:22:42.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have some photos here of Miss Rexroth,\N{\rCHT}我有幾張雷克諾斯小姐的照片{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.66,1:22:45.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,and that's the address that she's staying at.\N{\rCHT}這是她目前的位址{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.71,1:22:48.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is Mr. Smith's address. Massey's, Smith...\N{\rCHT}也是史密斯先生的地址 梅西的 史密斯…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.79,1:22:52.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's Mr. Smith's address. Although Mr. Smith is not directly involved.\N{\rCHT}雖然史密斯先生 並沒有參與這個活動{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.25,1:22:53.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because of an impending legal matter,\N{\rCHT}因法律所求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.96,1:22:56.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,we need this to happen within a certain time frame.\N{\rCHT}進行此事需要時間限制{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.38,1:22:59.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- On an expedited basis. - You're in a rush.\N{\rCHT}- 帶有迫切性 - 你們急{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.97,1:23:02.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,- We're not in a rush. - Mr. Smith is.\N{\rCHT}- 我們不急 - 史密斯先生急{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.44,1:23:15.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,She won't... She won't suffer, will she?\N{\rCHT}她不會… 她不會痛苦吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.44,1:23:18.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not unless you pay extra.\N{\rCHT}痛苦要額外收費{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.82,1:23:23.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ I've been workin' on the railroad ∮\N{\rCHT}我一直在鐵道上工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.28,1:23:25.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ All the livelong day ∮\N{\rCHT}每天每夜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.91,1:23:28.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ I've been workin' on the railroad ∮\N{\rCHT}我一直在鐵道上工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.46,1:23:31.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ Just to pass the time away ∮ \N{\rCHT}只為了消磨時間{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.75,1:23:35.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ Can't you hear the whistle blowin' ∮\N{\rCHT}聽見汽笛聲響了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.21,1:23:37.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ Rise up early in the... ∮\N{\rCHT}早起…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.76,1:23:43.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,∮ Whistles go "toot-toot." ∮\N{\rCHT}汽笛聲"嘟嘟"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.77,1:23:51.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Rexie?\N{\rCHT}小雷 怎麼了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.15,1:24:00.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello?\N{\rCHT}喂？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.95,1:24:05.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's here. One moment, please.\N{\rCHT}他在這裡 請稍後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.97,1:24:20.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miles.\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.59,1:24:23.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's for you.\N{\rCHT}找你的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.14,1:24:33.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello? Yes?\N{\rCHT}喂？是？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.28,1:24:44.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,What?\N{\rCHT}什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.49,1:24:48.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,I see.\N{\rCHT}知道了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.79,1:24:53.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,- My God. - What?\N{\rCHT}- 不得了 - 什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.96,1:24:58.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,That was Marvin Untermeyer. He was Rex Rexroth's personal attorney.\N{\rCHT}剛剛是雷克斯雷克諾斯 生前的律師馬文安特梅耶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.01,1:25:02.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes? What do you mean he was?\N{\rCHT}生前？什麼意思？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.18,1:25:07.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Rex had a massive coronary in the middle of a business meeting.\N{\rCHT}雷克斯開業務會議時心臟病發作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.14,1:25:09.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's dead.\N{\rCHT}死了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.31,1:25:14.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm very sorry to hear that, but you two weren't close, were you?\N{\rCHT}太不幸了 你們不是好朋友吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.69,1:25:19.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marvin said that Rex's will was four years old. Never redrafted it.\N{\rCHT}馬文說雷克斯四年前立了遺囑 一直沒有修改{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.44,1:25:23.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He was stinking rich. - Yes?\N{\rCHT}- 他非常有錢 - 然後呢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.12,1:25:28.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everything goes to Marylin.\N{\rCHT}一切盡歸瑪麗蓮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.67,1:25:39.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,She is exposed. No prenup. She's a sitting duck.\N{\rCHT}沒有婚前協議 她任人宰割{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.63,1:25:41.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,She's a sitting duck. Can't kill her. No need.\N{\rCHT}任人宰割 可割不可宰 不用殺{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.05,1:25:44.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,- No. It would be pointless. She's exposed. - It's pointless.\N{\rCHT}- 沒意義 她沒有防衛 - 沒意義{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.38,1:25:46.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why kill the only woman you've ever loved when she's the richer party?\N{\rCHT}她有錢 而你愛她 何必殺她？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.95,1:25:50.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,She's rich. And I love her. Don't need to kill her.\N{\rCHT}她有錢 而我愛她 不用殺她{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.43,1:25:51.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Ah! - What, "Ah"?\N{\rCHT}什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.06,1:25:53.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You've reached Wheezy Joe. - Joe!\N{\rCHT}- 我是氣喘喬 - 喬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.73,1:25:55.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you want?\N{\rCHT}有屁快放{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.27,1:25:58.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hi, it's Miles Smith... Mr. Smith calling to say,\N{\rCHT}我是邁爾斯史密斯… 史密斯先生要我說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.27,1:26:00.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,- on behalf of myself, that it is... - No-go.\N{\rCHT}- 我決定 這次… - 取消{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.57,1:26:02.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,No-go concerning Marylin.\N{\rCHT}我決定取消對瑪麗蓮的行動{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.94,1:26:06.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm speaking with no knowledge. This is what Mr. Smith wants.\N{\rCHT}我不知道行動內容 史密斯先生想取消{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.49,1:26:08.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is what I want.\N{\rCHT}我想取消{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.24,1:26:11.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am Mr. Smith. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}我是史密斯先生 謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.75,1:26:18.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That was good. - You think I'm protected?\N{\rCHT}- 說得好 - 我有保障嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.67,1:26:21.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Am I protected? - I think it would hold up.\N{\rCHT}- 我有保障嗎？- 庭上站得住腳{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.30,1:26:23.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Marylin. - Yes, yes. Marylin.\N{\rCHT}- 瑪麗蓮 - 對 瑪麗蓮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.21,1:26:25.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do we do? What if he's on his way there?\N{\rCHT}假如他正要去下手 怎麼辦？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.18,1:26:26.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes. Oh!\N{\rCHT}對{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.43,1:26:29.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,- If he's on his way there... - Oh, no! Marylin!\N{\rCHT}- 假如他正要去… - 不 瑪麗蓮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.89,1:26:33.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get her out and buy some time. Buy some time!\N{\rCHT}叫她出來爭取時間 爭取時間{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.11,1:26:41.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello?\N{\rCHT}喂？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.27,1:26:43.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, you must leave the house immediately.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 你要立刻離開這房子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.78,1:26:46.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's imperative that you leave the house. - Hello, Miles.\N{\rCHT}- 非常重要 - 邁爾斯 你好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.20,1:26:48.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hello, dear. - Now, Miles, pending final settlement,\N{\rCHT}- 你好 寶貝 - 邁爾斯 未定協議之前{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.87,1:26:50.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,you know that I'm entitled to use the house.\N{\rCHT}我有權住在這裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.15,1:26:52.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no, no! You don't understand, Marylin.\N{\rCHT}不 不 不 瑪麗蓮 你不明白{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.29,1:26:54.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's an emergency! Yes. - An emergency!\N{\rCHT}- 緊急事故 - 緊急事故{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.58,1:26:55.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,What is it?\N{\rCHT}什麼事故？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.66,1:26:59.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,I forgot that I left the gas main on, which leaks!\N{\rCHT}瓦斯漏氣 我忘記關開關{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.13,1:27:02.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Good gosh. That sounds dangerous. - It's a deadly, odorless, colorless,\N{\rCHT}- 聽起來好危險 - 瓦斯無臭無色無形{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.92,1:27:06.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,liquidless gas that attacks the central nervous system\N{\rCHT}會侵害神經系統{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.30,1:27:09.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,and causes diarrhea and facial tics!\N{\rCHT}引起腹瀉及面部抽搐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.34,1:27:11.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right.\N{\rCHT}好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.26,1:27:13.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well, thanks for calling, Miles. - Okay. Bye-bye.\N{\rCHT}- 邁爾斯 謝謝你打來 - 再見{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.48,1:27:17.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think she bought it.\N{\rCHT}她似乎相信了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.32,1:27:25.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, tell me,\N{\rCHT}告訴我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.57,1:27:30.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,who sent you?\N{\rCHT}是誰派你來的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.20,1:27:32.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Smith.\N{\rCHT}史密斯先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.91,1:27:35.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is this Mr. Smith?\N{\rCHT}這位是史密斯先生嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.54,1:27:37.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,No.\N{\rCHT}不{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.50,1:27:39.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's his lawyer.\N{\rCHT}那是他的律師{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.67,1:27:46.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whatever they're paying you, I'll double.\N{\rCHT}無論他們付你多少 我雙倍付你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.18,1:27:50.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,What now? We wait for Wheezy Joe.\N{\rCHT}- 現在怎麼樣？- 等氣喘喬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.84,1:27:52.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,We tell him it's a no-go.\N{\rCHT}跟他說取消{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.85,1:27:54.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Careful. Rottweilers.\N{\rCHT}小心惡狗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.94,1:28:04.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Looks like she's gone. Looks like she bought it.\N{\rCHT}她似乎走了 看來她信以為真{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.02,1:28:08.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good stuff. There's no one here. Except for the Rottweilers.\N{\rCHT}- 好了 這裡沒有人 - 除了惡狗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.61,1:28:11.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sure. Rottweilers.\N{\rCHT}對 惡狗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.91,1:28:14.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,You go that way.\N{\rCHT}你去那邊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.90,1:28:44.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wheezy Joe?\N{\rCHT}氣喘喬？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.93,1:29:20.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wheezy Joe, thank God you're in time.\N{\rCHT}氣喘喬 幸好你及時趕到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.93,1:29:24.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're not in time. We're in time. Thank God we're in time.\N{\rCHT}你來得不及時 幸好我們及時趕到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.73,1:29:27.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, it's a no-go. You get it?\N{\rCHT}取消行動 懂嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.48,1:29:30.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one need be the wiser, so you can just go on home.\N{\rCHT}不用驚動任何人 你可以回家去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.86,1:29:33.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Goodbye. You know, thank you so much.\N{\rCHT}再見 真的感謝你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.61,1:29:35.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hear that? Okay? No, no. No, no.\N{\rCHT}聽到了嗎？不 不 不{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.87,1:29:39.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no. No-go. No contract. It's off. It's...\N{\rCHT}取消了 不下手 中止行動…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.08,1:29:42.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Will you explain to the lunkhead? - No-go. It's a no-go.\N{\rCHT}- 你來說給呆頭鵝聽 - 取消 取消了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.96,1:29:46.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll settle your contract later. Look, you're fired, pal. Let it go. Walk away.\N{\rCHT}我們晚點再結算 你被炒魷魚了 走啦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.04,1:29:48.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Golden parachute. - Don't let the screen door hit you.\N{\rCHT}- 遣散 - 小心別撞到紗門{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.92,1:29:51.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Does he speak any language? - Here's what happened, Mr. Carnera.\N{\rCHT}- 他會說話嗎？- 卡內拉先生 是這樣的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.30,1:29:53.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,We feel that...\N{\rCHT}我們覺得…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.17,1:29:54.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait, wait, wait.\N{\rCHT}等一下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.53,1:30:13.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wheezy!\N{\rCHT}氣喘喬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.21,1:30:30.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Told him it was a no-go.\N{\rCHT}就跟他說取消了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.99,1:30:56.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Gentlemen. - Freddy.\N{\rCHT}- 兩位好 - 佛萊迪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.62,1:31:03.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hello, Marylin. - Hello, Miles.\N{\rCHT}- 你好 瑪麗蓮 - 你好 邁爾斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.20,1:31:09.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,- This is where we first met, remember? - Of course I remember.\N{\rCHT}- 我們在這裡初見面 記得嗎？- 當然記得{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.92,1:31:13.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that when you walk out that door today,\N{\rCHT}可惜今天你走出那扇門之後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.55,1:31:16.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,you'll be walking out of my life forever.\N{\rCHT}就永遠走出我的人生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.55,1:31:19.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not something I wanted either.\N{\rCHT}我也無可奈何{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.55,1:31:21.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,But then, I guess\N{\rCHT}不過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.97,1:31:25.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,something inside of me died\N{\rCHT}當我知道你買兇殺我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.39,1:31:29.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,when I realized that you'd hired a goon to kill me.\N{\rCHT}我不得不死心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.15,1:31:32.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Wait a minute. You hired him to kill me. - No. Both of you wait a minute.\N{\rCHT}- 等等 你買兇殺我 - 不 你們都別說了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.52,1:31:35.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Nobody hired anyone to kill anyone. - Hear, hear.\N{\rCHT}- 誰也沒有買兇殺人 - 像真的一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.36,1:31:38.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Apparently, from what I can gather, a burglar broke into your house.\N{\rCHT}我只知道有人進你的房子行竊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.86,1:31:41.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Miles' house. - Whatever!\N{\rCHT}- 邁爾斯的房子 - 隨便啦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.57,1:31:45.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,A burglar broke in intending to loot the place, repented,\N{\rCHT}賊人正想搜掠 突然悔過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.83,1:31:49.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,became despondent over his lifestyle and shot himself.\N{\rCHT}自慚形穢 無地自容 吞槍自盡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.79,1:31:55.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So where does that leave you and me? - Well, we've outlined a settlement.\N{\rCHT}- 那麼你我怎麼辦？- 我們擬定了一份協議初稿{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.09,1:31:56.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,We think it's very generous.\N{\rCHT}條件非常優厚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.55,1:32:00.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,My client is prepared to consider a reconciliation.\N{\rCHT}我的客戶願意考慮和解{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.89,1:32:03.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,But how could I trust you, Miles, after all this?\N{\rCHT}邁爾斯 出了這麼多事 我怎麼信任你？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.14,1:32:04.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,See, that's exactly right. The point is...\N{\rCHT}說得對極了 重點是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.81,1:32:06.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,You wounded me first, Marylin.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 你先傷我的心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.06,1:32:11.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not proud of what I've done, but God knows, I did trust you once.\N{\rCHT}我過去所為不光彩 但我信任過你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.15,1:32:16.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you could just give us another chance.\N{\rCHT}假如你肯多給我們一次機會{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.19,1:32:18.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, if you'll pardon me here,\N{\rCHT}不好意思{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.15,1:32:21.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,but I think my client is well beyond the point of considering...\N{\rCHT}但我相信我的客戶不會…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.32,1:32:25.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,How could I ever trust you again? I mean really trust you, Miles?\N{\rCHT}我要怎樣才能信任你？邁爾斯 真正信任你？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.13,1:32:43.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin, there is nothing in the Massey prenup that says\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮 梅西婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.72,1:32:47.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,it can't be executed after the parties wed.\N{\rCHT}婚後簽依然有效{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.77,1:32:52.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, if this indeed is a Massey prenup,\N{\rCHT}這份真的是梅西婚前協議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.81,1:32:57.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,and a cursory examination tends to support that it is, then...\N{\rCHT}假如真是梅西婚前協議…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.36,1:33:03.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, Marylin. You're exposed.\N{\rCHT}天啊 瑪麗蓮 你沒有防衛了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.16,1:33:08.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marylin.\N{\rCHT}瑪麗蓮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.09,1:33:21.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Counselor! Freddy!\N{\rCHT}律師 佛萊迪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.22,1:33:23.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy! Come on, Freddy! No fair!\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪 這不公平{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.68,1:33:25.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Freddy!\N{\rCHT}佛萊迪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.73,1:33:34.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Did you hear something? - Only the patter of little lawyers' feet.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼聲音？- 小律師在互相追逐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.03,1:33:43.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where did you find Howard?\N{\rCHT}你從哪裡找來霍爾的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.82,1:33:48.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,The actor? From a TV producer. I think you know him.\N{\rCHT}那個演員？一個電視製片介紹的 我想你認識他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.74,1:33:52.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,I gave him an idea for a new show, so he made me a partner.\N{\rCHT}我給他新節目的靈感 他讓我做合夥人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.29,1:34:01.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I guess that means I'm a partner. - I guess it does.\N{\rCHT}- 那麼我大概也成為合夥人了 - 大概是吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.47,1:34:07.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,And what exactly is it we're partners in?\N{\rCHT}什麼的合夥人？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.35,1:34:17.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who gets what, and who gets who?\N{\rCHT}誰占到資產？誰占到便宜？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.02,1:34:21.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll find out on America's Funniest Divorce Videos.\N{\rCHT}答案在《離婚歡笑一籮筐》{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.07,1:34:25.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here's the star of our show, Gus Petch!\N{\rCHT}本節目的明星主持人 蓋斯派奇{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.91,1:34:33.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,You goddamn right, folks. I'm Gus Petch. And we got a great show for you.\N{\rCHT}我正是蓋斯派奇 本節目精彩百出{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.91,1:34:36.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,We gonna make you laugh. We gonna make you cry.\N{\rCHT}我們會令你笑 令你哭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.58,1:34:41.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,- But most of all, we gonna nail your ass! - Ass!\N{\rCHT}- 最重要的是 我們會把你逮個正著 - 逮個正著{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.88,1:34:44.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nail your ass!\N{\rCHT}逮個正著{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.09,1:34:48.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nail your ass! Nail your ass!\N{\rCHT}逮個正著 逮個正著{\r}
